(16463393, '', 'Applicant 21', 1622965, 'Pendle Sculpture Trail', 11, 15.0, 'No', 'REJECTED', 0, 0, 5, 'Q1', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 0, 'Organisation', 'North West', 'Pendle', 'Lancashire', 'Pendle', 0, 'Y', 0, '12 weeks', 12, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Visual arts', '#REF!', 'North West', 'Pendle Sculpture Trail will bring natural art forms, created by local artists into Aitken Wood. The trail will have pieces that will inspire and embrace the local environment. The artistic variety of sculptures will provoke debate amongst local communities and schools, as well as attracting visitors to Pendle.'),
(16463929, '', 'Applicant 22', 7653984, 'VAIL Programme: Stakeholders and Audiences 2011', 11, 48.0, 'No', 'OFFERED', 48, 36, 5, 'Q1', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 1, 'Organisation', 'North West', 'Liverpool, Riverside', 'Merseyside', 'Liverpool', 31, 'N', 1, '12 weeks', 12, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Visual arts', '#REF!', 'North West', 'This bid aims to support a region-wide project that builds capacity, encourages cross-regional visits and supports the artistic community. \nThere are three main areas of focus for this application: a stakeholder perception survey, an audience research exercise and a region-wide event.'),
