(16538435, '', 'Applicant 45', 16538428, 'Bede - A play with music, verse and prose.', 18, 34.0, 'No', 'REJECTED', 34, 0, 5, 'Q1', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 0, 'Organisation', 'North East', 'South Shields', 'Tyne and Wear', 'South Tyneside', 0, 'Y', 0, '12 weeks', 11, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Theatre', '#REF!', 'North East', 'Bede is a drama with music, prose and verse about The Venerable Bede (672 - 735 A.D.).  We wish to promote knowledge and interest in Bede the man and the area he grew up in: at the same time examining aspects of faith and belief which still have relevance today.'),
(16538817, '', 'Applicant 46', 13168508, 'SATSYMPH: ''On a theme of Hermes''', 19, 17.0, 'No', 'OFFERED', 17, 17, 6, 'Q1', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 1, 'Individual', 'South West', 'Yeovil', 'Somerset', 'South Somerset', 18, 'N', 1, '12 weeks', 11, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Combined arts', '#REF!', 'South West', 'A fusion of contemporary music and poetry uniquely delivered through innovative mobile technologies that is user-directed and geo-located. It responds to where the user is, morphing according to what the user does. This is an entirely new music/poetry paradigm with national/international impact / distribution'),
(16544229, '', 'Applicant 47', 16544223, 'Flourish', 19, 19.0, 'No', 'REJECTED', 19, 0, 6, 'Q1', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 0, 'Individual', 'London', 'Lewisham, Deptford', 'Greater London', 'Lewisham', 0, 'Y', 0, '12 weeks', 11, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Visual arts', '#REF!', 'London', 'Flourish showcases artwork by care-experienced children and young people from around the UK, aged 0'),
(16547434, '', 'Applicant 48', 1847522, 'Two Peacocks', 19, 37.0, 'No', 'OFFERED', 37, 37, 6, 'Q1', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 1, 'Individual', 'London', 'Poplar and Limehouse', 'Greater London', 'Tower Hamlets', 13, 'N', 1, '12 weeks', 11, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Visual arts', '#REF!', 'London', 'Two Peacocks is a collaborative installation at Gallery North in Newcastle incorporating new commissions by artists working in a wide range of media, taking the form of a Department Store, questioning received notions of the white cube. Integral to the project are a series of educational workshops engaging new audiences.'),
(16549100, '', 'Applicant 49', 1630524, 'Collaborate', 18, 66.0, 'No', 'OFFERED', 66, 66, 6, 'Q1', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 1, 'Organisation', 'South West', 'North East Somerset', 'Bath and North East Somerset', 'Bath and North East Somerset', 5, 'N', 1, '12 weeks', 11, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Combined arts', '#REF!', 'South West', 'Collaborate will support Creativity Works through a period of transition at the start of our new 5 year Strategic Plan.  It will contribute to developing our partnership and artistic skills and will ensure that we are in a position to build on our previous work into a sustainable future.'),
(16549288, '', 'Applicant 50', 16549275, 'In the Know', 19, 36.0, 'No', 'OFFERED', 36, 36, 6, 'Q1', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 1, 'Organisation', 'West Midlands', 'Birmingham, Selly Oak', 'West Midlands', 'Birmingham', 3, 'N', 1, '12 weeks', 11, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Visual arts', '#REF!', 'West Midlands', '''In the Know'' is located in Stirchley,  primarily a residential area with a declining shopping street (& one of the main routes into Birmingham).  Utilising site-specific performance and visual art we will work with people to define the cultural values and assets of the neighborhood and explore possibilities for regeneration.\n'),
(16550957, '', 'Applicant 51', 16550955, 'The Red Sulphur or The Alchemy of the Soul', 20, 13.0, 'No', 'REJECTED', 0, 0, 6, 'Q1', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 0, 'Individual', 'London', 'Carshalton and Wallington', 'Greater London', 'Sutton', 0, 'Y', 0, '12 weeks', 11, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Visual arts', '#REF!', 'London', 'The Red Sulphur is an installation that looks at the transformation of the human spirit.  It is about dealing with the restriction of trials and the hope of fulfilment, and the need to maintain values. I intend to run workshops, looking at the themes, aimed at varying age groups.'),
(16564201, '', 'Applicant 52', 16564194, 'Project Pressure', 17, 18.0, 'No', 'REJECTED', 0, 0, 6, 'Q1', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 0, 'Organisation', 'London', 'Hackney South and Shoreditch', 'Greater London', 'Hackney', 0, 'N', 0, '12 weeks', 11, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Visual arts', '#REF!', 'London', 'Project Pressure''s goal is to photograph and exhibit the world''s vanishing and receding glaciers and to document the environmental impact of climate change. Project Pressure is a not-for-profit organisation set out to generate the world''s first photographic glacier atlas. Art being the media of engagement.'),
(16566968, '', 'Applicant 53', 1602512, 'The Simple Things In Life', 19, 62.0, 'No', 'OFFERED', 62, 62, 14, 'Q1', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', 'National activities', 1, 'Organisation', 'London', 'Battersea', 'Greater London', 'Wandsworth', 27, 'N', 1, '12 weeks', 12, 0, 0, 'Ot', 'Theatre', '#REF!', 'London', 'Fuel is planning a new project to celebrate the simple things in life. It'),
(16567070, '', 'Applicant 54', 1617433, 'Dance Studio Launch Programme 2011-2012', 19, 20.0, 'No', 'OFFERED', 20, 20, 5, 'Q1', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 1, 'Organisation', 'North West', 'Barrow and Furness', 'Cumbria', 'Barrow-in-Furness', 3, 'N', 1, '12 weeks', 11, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Dance', '#REF!', 'North West', 'Our Dance Studio Launch Programme focuses on offering children and Young People living in this Super Output ward  the opportunity to experience the richness of the Arts as participants and audience; bringing passionate, innovative and experienced Associate Artists and Media Practitioners to collaborate with them in making new work /performance.'),
(16567348, '', 'Applicant 55', 1623758, 'Deaf Child - Hero Child', 20, 95.0, 'No', 'OFFERED', 95, 95, 14, 'Q1', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', 'National activities', 1, 'Organisation', 'South East', 'Brighton, Pavilion', 'Brighton and Hove', 'Brighton and Hove', 4, 'N', 1, '12 weeks', 12, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Theatre', '#REF!', 'South East', 'We will create two theatrical stories for deaf & hearing children that have visible, articulate and resilient Deaf child characters as central; allow an emerging Deaf director to develop, and re-appoint an `Associate Artist'),
(16567458, '', 'Applicant 56', 1612369, 'The NETWORK project', 20, 30.0, 'No', 'OFFERED', 30, 30, 19, 'Q1', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 1, 'Organisation', 'North East', 'Gateshead', 'Tyne and Wear', 'Gateshead', 6, 'Y', 1, '12 weeks', 13, 0, 0, 'Ot', 'Music', '#REF!', 'North East', 'The NETWORK project aims to offer refugees and asylum seekers opportunities to develop their skills in performing arts and arts administration. It will develop the regional hub of a national initiative Platforma. The project will match refugees with arts professionals in a buddy relationship.'),
(16575351, '', 'Applicant 57', 9915709, 'Regional tour of Somebody''s Son production', 21, 37.0, 'No', 'REJECTED', 37, 0, 14, 'Q1', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', 'National activities', 0, 'Individual', 'Yorkshire and The Humber', 'Sheffield, Brightside and Hillsborough', 'South Yorkshire', 'Sheffield', 0, 'N', 0, '12 weeks', 12, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Theatre', '#REF!', 'Yorkshire', 'The proposed activity is a final draft of Somebody''s Son, regional tour of Somebody''s Son with dates in London. Marcia Layne and Amanda Huxtable to undertake professional development in producing a tour. The tour will be co-produced by writer, director and freelance producer.'),
(16583935, '', 'Applicant 58', 16583933, 'Welcome to Nollywood', 1, 3.0, 'Yes', 'REJECTED', 0, 0, 3, 'Q1', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 0, 'Individual', 'West Midlands', 'Solihull', 'West Midlands', 'Solihull', 0, 'N', 0, '6 weeks', 5, 1, 1, 'Ot', 'Visual arts', '#REF!', 'West Midlands', 'The project is set to initiate a cross-cultural dialogue centred around acquiring a home made projector from Nigerian filmmaker Izu Ojukwu. The object ties in with a larger field of enquiry in relation to questions of production and distribution and is suitable for schools, film societies, museums and exhibitions.'),
(16590910, '', 'Applicant 59', 1626383, 'Nightingale Theatre building', 24, 85.0, 'No', 'OFFERED', 85, 85, 19, 'Q1', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 1, 'Organisation', 'South East', 'Brighton, Pavilion', 'Brighton and Hove', 'Brighton and Hove', 17, 'Y', 1, '12 weeks', 12, 0, 0, 'Ot', 'Theatre', '#REF!', 'South East', 'All aspects of the artistic, residence and performance  programme happening within the spaces of the Nightingale Theatre over a period of 18months to include two full Brighton Fringe Festivals.'),
(16600496, '', 'Applicant 60', 1622487, 'Fit for the Future Programme', 24, 70.0, 'No', 'REJECTED', 0, 0, 19, 'Q1', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 0, 'Organisation', 'North West', 'Liverpool, Riverside', 'Merseyside', 'Liverpool', 0, 'N', 0, '12 weeks', 12, 0, 0, 'Ot', 'Not art form specific', '#REF!', 'North West', 'Aimed at small to medium cultural organisations in receipt of funding from both Liverpool City Council and other public sector organisations.\n\nThis will be a series of seminars and workshops providing specialised advice to organisations in order for them to become more sustainable and less reliant on public sector funding. \n'),
(16615536, '', 'Applicant 61', 1601759, 'LONSAS Outreach', 24, 40.0, 'No', 'OFFERED', 40, 40, 19, 'Q1', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 1, 'Organisation', 'London', 'Holborn and St Pancras', 'Greater London', 'Camden', 3, 'N', 1, '12 weeks', 12, 0, 0, 'Ot', 'Not art form specific', '#REF!', 'London', 'Build on the success and network of the London Schools Arts Service (LONSAS) to develop a series of outreach measures that will encourage more schools to engage with the arts.\n\nThe activity will focus on arts opportunities for schools and education settings but is not curriculum based.'),
(16615613, '', 'Applicant 62', 9213091, 'The Firestation Residents Programme', 24, 52.0, 'No', 'OFFERED', 0, 52, 6, 'Q1', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 1, 'Organisation', 'South East', 'Windsor', 'Windsor and Maidenhead', 'Windsor and Maidenhead', 10, 'Y', 1, '12 weeks', 10, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Combined arts', '#REF!', 'South East', 'The Firestation''s Residents Programme works with professional artists and companies, offering a supportive environment to develop creative practice and artistic visions.\n\nIt offers participants expert support, a cultural home, work space, stability and an audience to help develop their work and now looks to commission and tour new works.'),
(16615815, '', 'Applicant 63', 8536738, 'The production of The Four Stages Of Cruelty', 24, 24.0, 'No', 'OFFERED', 24, 24, 6, 'Q1', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 1, 'Organisation', 'London', 'Hampstead and Kilburn', 'Greater London', 'Brent', 21, 'Y', 1, '12 weeks', 10, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Theatre', '#REF!', 'London', 'To produce The Four Stages of Cruelty, based on a series of engravings by William Hogarth, using 9\nactors, a writer, director, designer and producer,  at Arcola Theatre in May and June 2011.'),
(16644554, '', 'Applicant 64', 16644547, 'Death''s Cabaret - A Love Story', 21, 45.0, 'No', 'OFFERED', 45, 45, 14, 'Q1', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', 'National activities', 1, 'Organisation', 'South East', 'South West Surrey', 'Surrey', 'Waverley', 4, 'Y', 1, '12 weeks', 12, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Music', '#REF!', 'South East', 'Death''s Cabaret: A 50 minute instrumental, vocal and narrative music-theatre work. A unique and thrilling marriage of the C19th concerto form with the grime and sensuality of cabaret for theatre, concert-hall and found spaces. In partnership with ''Beyond Borders.'' English and Scottish tour to 10 venues.'),
(16645028, '', 'Applicant 65', 1843647, 'Quietus: containing the human body in death', 26, 86.0, 'No', 'REJECTED', 0, 0, 14, 'Q1', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', 'National activities', 0, 'Individual', 'London', 'Dulwich and West Norwood', 'Greater London', 'Southwark', 0, 'Y', 0, '12 weeks', 11, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Visual arts', '#REF!', 'London', 'My activity is a touring exhibition of contemporary ceramics addressing the containment of the human body in death. Quietus (release from life; death) will present artist made funerary works, including cinerary jars and monumental sarcophagi, and offer alternative means of engaging specialist and non-specialist audiences in this challenging subject.\n\n'),
(16645221, '', 'Applicant 66', 1388406, 'Digital Darlings', 26, 80.0, 'No', 'REJECTED', 0, 0, 19, 'Q1', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 0, 'Organisation', 'Yorkshire and The Humber', 'Huddersfield', 'West Yorkshire', 'Kirklees', 0, 'Y', 0, '12 weeks', 12, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Literature', '#REF!', 'Yorkshire', 'Our activity is based online and enables children and young people to create web pages and printed books based on their own creative content .  The books will be personalised and printed using digital printing technology which will enable each child taking part to have their own book'),
(16645488, '', 'Applicant 67', 1637673, 'Collaborations and Partnerships - a way forward', 24, 25.0, 'No', 'OFFERED', 25, 25, 19, 'Q1', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 1, 'Organisation', 'Yorkshire and The Humber', 'East Yorkshire', 'East Riding of Yorkshire', 'East Riding of Yorkshire', 7, 'Y', 1, '12 weeks', 12, 0, 0, 'Ot', 'Music', '#REF!', 'Yorkshire', 'Help develop the festival in terms of our audiences, and future suitability by forging partnerships and collaborations with other local organisations having an interest in arts and related activities. This will help us achieve the Aims and Objectives as set out in our Business Plan.'),
(16645888, '', 'Applicant 68', 1603661, 'FOUNDRY 2011', 21, 69.0, 'No', 'OFFERED', 69, 69, 20, 'Q1', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 1, 'Organisation', 'South East', 'South West Surrey', 'Surrey', 'Waverley', 4, 'Y', 1, '12 weeks', 13, 0, 0, 'Ot', 'Theatre', '#REF!', 'South East', 'FOUNDRY 2011 proposes to develop and showcase KABADDI-KABADDI-KABADDI by Satinder Chohan  at South Hill Park, Bracknell (May 2011); produce and tour KALASHNIKOV: IN THE WOODS BY THE LAKE by Fraser Grace (Autumn 2011) and develop a sutainable touring network for the company as part of our organisational development.'),
(16646037, '', 'Applicant 69', 1613854, 'Publishing Programme of work', 19, 19.0, 'No', 'OFFERED', 19, 19, 5, 'Q1', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 1, 'Organisation', 'North East', 'Tynemouth', 'Tyne and Wear', 'North Tyneside', 19, 'N', 1, '12 weeks', 11, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Literature', '#REF!', 'North East', 'IRON Press plans to publish six new books to enhance its reputation as a leading independent UK\nliterary publisher.The list includes one haiku collection, one haiku anthology, a short story collection. a short story anthology, and two collections of poetry.'),
(16646412, '', 'Applicant 70', 16646405, 'Pembroke Academy of Music', 23, 13.0, 'No', 'REJECTED', 0, 0, 6, 'Q1', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 0, 'Organisation', 'London', 'Bermondsey and Old Southwark', 'Greater London', 'Southwark', 0, 'N', 0, '12 weeks', 10, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Music', '#REF!', 'London', 'The Pembroke Academy of Music is an open access music school for young people aged 8 to 18 in the deprived area of Walworth. Featuring instrumental tuition, theory tuition and choral practice, the Academy offers a valuable opportunity for young people to gain a musical skill.'),
(16646709, '', 'Applicant 71', 1602797, 'The Olympic Nations - A Spectacular in Song', 20, 18.0, 'No', 'REJECTED', 0, 0, 6, 'Q1', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 0, 'Organisation', 'London', 'Cities of London and Westminster', 'Greater London', 'Westminster', 0, 'Y', 0, '12 weeks', 11, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Music', '#REF!', 'London', 'Concerts for older people in all Greater London Boroughs EXCLUDING the Five Olympic Boroughs.'),
(16646781, '', 'Applicant 72', 16646774, 'Test Space: Hub', 24, 84.0, 'No', 'REJECTED', 0, 0, 5, 'Q1', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 0, 'Organisation', 'Yorkshire and The Humber', 'Leeds North East', 'West Yorkshire', 'Leeds', 0, 'N', 0, '12 weeks', 10, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Combined arts', '#REF!', 'Yorkshire', 'Taking over empty space in Leeds, Test Space will develop a creative hub in the City Centre. The Test Space hub will offer opportunities for creatives to network, collaborate and showcase work to other artists, businesses and the public. It will be a space to play, perform and test ideas.'),
(16647072, '', 'Applicant 73', 1386291, 'Deaf Migrant Project', 25, 30.0, 'No', 'OFFERED', 30, 30, 6, 'Q1', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 1, 'Organisation', 'London', 'Holborn and St Pancras', 'Greater London', 'Camden', 20, 'Y', 1, '12 weeks', 10, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Theatre', '#REF!', 'London', 'A theatre piece created by Deaf Artistic Director Paula Garfield, and supported by Punch Drunk and Theatre de Complicite, based on the real life experiences of Deaf Migrants, performed by a mixed cast of deaf and hearing actors, and accessible to both deaf and hearing audiences'),
(16660323, '', 'Applicant 74', 1590382, 'Arts Fresco 2011', 23, 55.0, 'No', 'OFFERED', 55, 55, 6, 'Q1', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 1, 'Organisation', 'East Midlands', 'Harborough', 'Leicestershire', 'Harborough', 19, 'Y', 1, '12 weeks', 10, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Theatre', '#REF!', 'East Midlands', 'Arts Fresco is an annual street arts event celebrating outdoor performance arts. It aims to engage with people who have little contact with live performance and to promote life-long interest in the arts. Typically we include commissioned and workshop pieces to increase audience interaction and develop artistic skills.'),
(16667031, '', 'Applicant 75', 1613036, 'Hexham Abbey Festival of Music & Arts 2011', 23, 27.0, 'No', 'OFFERED', 27, 27, 5, 'Q1', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 1, 'Organisation', 'North East', 'Hexham', 'Northumberland', 'Northumberland', 15, 'Y', 1, '12 weeks', 10, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Combined arts', '#REF!', 'North East', 'Presentation of 9 day annual festival of high quality professional music (including classical, early, new, traditional & jazz), arts (including film, theatre, exhibition) in Hexham Abbey and other local venues. Themed Art as Science: Science as Art, focuses on accessibility, community involvement, rare, contemporary & new work, Young Artist Platform, commissions.'),
(16667251, '', 'Applicant 76', 1619262, 'The Unthanks and Brighouse and Rastrick Band', 26, 38.0, 'No', 'OFFERED', 38, 38, 14, 'Q1', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', 'National activities', 1, 'Organisation', 'North West', 'Oldham East and Saddleworth', 'Greater Manchester', 'Oldham', 5, 'Y', 1, '12 weeks', 11, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Music', '#REF!', 'North West', 'Root Music wishes to work in partnership with BRASS '),
(16678070, '', 'Applicant 77', 1620756, 'Dashehra Diwali Mela 2011', 26, 40.0, 'No', 'REJECTED', 0, 0, 19, 'Q1', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 0, 'Organisation', 'North West', 'Manchester, Withington', 'Greater Manchester', 'Manchester', 0, 'Y', 0, '12 weeks', 12, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Combined arts', '#REF!', 'North West', 'Dashehra Diwali Mela 2011\nMain elements are:\nRavan show and fireworks\nPre-event lantern making in schools\nPre-event dance development workshops\nArts and crafts, dance and puppet show and workshops on the day of the event\nLarge wearable lanterns\nStage performances and street theatre\nYouth Dance Competition\n`TRUNK'),
(16692387, '', 'Applicant 78', 1600890, 'Falling Up', 24, 41.0, 'No', 'OFFERED', 41, 41, 19, 'Q1', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 1, 'Organisation', 'London', 'Hackney South and Shoreditch', 'Greater London', 'Hackney', 18, 'N', 1, '12 weeks', 12, 0, 0, 'Ot', 'Theatre', '#REF!', 'London', 'Falling Up is the creation and production of a touring acrobatic performance with 4 female performers for street theatre or unconventional venues, including an outreach programme of physical workshops. Through 4 personal journeys, rooted in the relationship between each performer and her body, it will reflect on bigger social issues.'),
(16700793, '', 'Applicant 79', 1620819, 'Titanic', 27, 100.0, 'No', 'OFFERED', 100, 100, 19, 'Q1', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 1, 'Organisation', 'North West', 'Liverpool, Riverside', 'Merseyside', 'Liverpool', 20, 'Y', 1, '12 weeks', 12, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Theatre', '#REF!', 'North West', 'In April 2012 to commemorate the 100th anniversary of the sinking of The Titanic, Liverpool City Council will commission a large scale piece of street theatre delivered by Royal Deluxe. The piece will take play out over 4 days on the streets of North Liverpool and Liverpool City Centre.'),
(16703444, '', 'Applicant 80', 16703434, 'London Street Photography Festival', 28, 83.0, 'No', 'REJECTED', 0, 0, 19, 'Q1', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 0, 'Organisation', 'London', 'Hackney South and Shoreditch', 'Greater London', 'Hackney', 0, 'N', 0, '12 weeks', 12, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Visual arts', '#REF!', 'London', 'The London Street Photography Festival will be the first of its kind in the UK '),
(16711095, '', 'Applicant 81', 1386429, 'The Alternative Village Fete', 28, 44.0, 'No', 'OFFERED', 44, 44, 14, 'Q1', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', 'National activities', 1, 'Organisation', 'London', 'Vauxhall', 'Greater London', 'Lambeth', 17, 'Y', 1, '12 weeks', 11, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Combined arts', '#REF!', 'London', 'Using the concept of the Traditional British Village Fete to create a free event in a public space, the project brings together a programme of innovative, accessible live art and performance with craft, food produce and participatory activities for a wide ranging audience, encompassing young, old, arts and mainstream.');
