(16990856, '', 'Applicant 314', 16990854, 'Utopian Realism', 1, 6.0, 'No', 'OFFERED', 6, 6, 5, 'Q1', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 1, 'Individual', 'North East', 'Hexham', 'Northumberland', 'Northumberland', 13, 'N', 1, '6 weeks', 5, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Visual arts', '#REF!', 'North East', 'Utopian Realism will focus on the evolution of radical ideas in rural places and their impact upon the wider world. By looking to the past for solutions for the future visual artists Bridget Kennedy and Mair Hughes will make and exhibit new visual artworks based on findings in their neighbourhoods.\n'),
(16993234, '', 'Applicant 315', 15875965, 'David Hoyle''s Lives 2', 1, 5.0, 'No', 'REJECTED', 5, 0, 5, 'Q1', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 0, 'Individual', 'London', 'Lewisham West and Penge', 'Greater London', 'Bromley', 0, 'N', 0, '6 weeks', 5, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Theatre', '#REF!', 'London', 'We are applying for funding for another run of six weekly shows staring performance artist David Hoyle with a selection of special guests. The shows will take place at the Royal Vauxhall Tavern in London and will be open to anyone over 18 years of age.'),
(16993330, '', 'Applicant 316', 16993323, 'Word Up! Festival', 1, 37.0, 'No', 'OFFERED', 37, 37, 18, 'Q1', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 1, 'Organisation', 'London', 'Dulwich and West Norwood', 'Greater London', 'Lambeth', 2, 'N', 1, '12 weeks', 11, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Combined arts', '#REF!', 'London', 'A new annual 3-day festival of books and arts for children and families in south London which will feature a high profile line up of children'),
(16995377, '', 'Applicant 317', 16995370, 'B Sharp Organisational Development', 1, 9.0, 'No', 'OFFERED', 9, 9, 6, 'Q1', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 1, 'Organisation', 'South West', 'West Dorset', 'Dorset', 'West Dorset', 16, 'Y', 1, '6 weeks', 5, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Music', '#REF!', 'South West', 'Improve Lyme Youth Arts (B Sharp) as an organisation, its structure, skill level and ability to grow in a sustainable way.\n\nDecrease financial dependence on piecemeal grants - increase income portfolio.\n;\nIncrease regional awareness and the number and diversity of partner organisations to work with.\n'),
(16995509, '', 'Applicant 318', 1487286, 'FREEDOM 2011', 2, 99.0, 'No', 'OFFERED', 99, 99, 31, 'Q1', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 1, 'Organisation', 'Yorkshire and The Humber', 'Beverley and Holderness', 'East Riding of Yorkshire', 'East Riding of Yorkshire', 6, 'Y', 1, '12 weeks', 13, 0, 0, 'Ot', 'Combined arts', '#REF!', 'Yorkshire', 'FREEDOM is an annual arts festival in Hull, showcasing high impact, innovative, international quality street and performance arts events celebrating and promoting concepts of Freedom and liberty. The programme includes music and spoken word events, street performances, and site specific work.  This application is for the 2011 event.'),
(16995651, '', 'Applicant 319', 16995649, 'Dan Sherer''s Writer Development application', 1, 5.0, 'No', 'OFFERED', 5, 5, 5, 'Q1', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 1, 'Individual', 'Eastern', 'Harwich and North Essex', 'Essex', 'Colchester', 18, 'N', 1, '6 weeks', 5, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Theatre', '#REF!', 'East', 'A period of professional development as a playwright, away from the responsibilities of my other creative roles of director and Artistic Director. I intend to develop my skill set as a playwright through mentorship; develop my unique writing process through practice; and develop my writing scope though `going and seeing'),
(16995724, '', 'Applicant 320', 1623554, 'Chifest - Chichester Festivities Fringe', 1, 2.0, 'No', 'REJECTED', 0, 0, 6, 'Q1', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 0, 'Organisation', 'South East', 'Chichester', 'West Sussex', 'Chichester', 0, 'Y', 0, '6 weeks', 5, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Combined arts', '#REF!', 'South East', 'We are organising an 8 day Fringe festival to engage Chichester''s amateur and semi-professional artists with a wider audience. Our focus will be the city centre, using streets, shops, cafes, pubs, parks and smaller venues to reach audiences who may not otherwise experience art, performance or live music.'),
(16995850, '', 'Applicant 321', 15950131, 'Giving Into Gift', 1, 7.0, 'No', 'OFFERED', 7, 7, 5, 'Q1', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 1, 'Individual', 'North West', 'Liverpool, Walton', 'Merseyside', 'Liverpool', 15, 'N', 1, '6 weeks', 5, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Visual arts', '#REF!', 'North West', 'Concerned with gift and donative art in public space, Everyone''s Got One is an artist commission and\ndevelopment program for 6 artists, and an opportunity for the display on Liverpool''s BBC Big Screen for\ngift-themed photographs submitted by the public.'),
(16995935, '', 'Applicant 322', 16995933, 'ORDINARY WOMAN', 1, 9.0, 'No', 'REJECTED', 0, 0, 6, 'Q1', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 0, 'Individual', 'South East', 'Hove', 'Brighton and Hove', 'Brighton and Hove', 0, 'N', 0, '6 weeks', 5, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Theatre', '#REF!', 'South East', 'ORDINARY WOMAN is a new play with songs about disability and postnatal depression. It uses the music of Sheryl Crow to express the epic emotions roused within domesticity. With support, it will have its initial workshop and performances in the education studio of the Theatre Royal Newcastle in August 2011.'),
(16996008, '', 'Applicant 323', 16395364, 'Episodes of Blackness', 2, 10.0, 'No', 'OFFERED', 10, 10, 5, 'Q1', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 1, 'Individual', 'London', 'Tottenham', 'Greater London', 'Haringey', 20, 'N', 1, '6 weeks', 5, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Combined arts', '#REF!', 'London', 'Episodes of Blackness is an interdisciplinary dance, music and spoken word performance created by Alesandra Seutin. Comprising Word! and Kwenda-Kwenda these works will make a distinctly African fast paced and athletic evening of contemporary work responding to current issues and with relevance for diverse audiences.'),
