(16997721, '', 'Applicant 326', 16997719, 'BRITONS', 2, 25.0, 'No', 'REJECTED', 25, 0, 1, 'Q1', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 0, 'Individual', 'London', 'Poplar and Limehouse', 'Greater London', 'Tower Hamlets', 0, 'Y', 0, '12 weeks', 13, 0, 0, 'Ot', 'Visual arts', '#REF!', 'London', 'BRITONS is an Olympics 2012-related outdoor photographic exhibition featuring a diverse range of British people - famous and anonymous. The subjects will be drawn from all over the UK - captured by award-winning photographer Tom Stoddart. BRITONS will be free, accessible to all and celebratory in nature.'),
(16999092, '', 'Applicant 327', 16999085, 'Painting, sculpture, photography, needlecraft', 1, 5.0, 'No', 'OFFERED', 5, 5, 12, 'Q1', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 1, 'Organisation', 'Yorkshire and The Humber', 'Beverley and Holderness', 'East Riding of Yorkshire', 'East Riding of Yorkshire', 4, 'N', 1, '6 weeks', 6, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Visual arts', '#REF!', 'Yorkshire', 'This is a new group, launched in October 2010 at our annual charity Heritage Weekend.  Open to all residents, using existing village hall, its purpose is social cohesion by developing art and craft skills by sharing local expertise and buying in skilled tutors.'),
(16999158, '', 'Applicant 328', 1618867, 'Manchester Tales', 1, 8.0, 'No', 'OFFERED', 8, 8, 5, 'Q1', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 1, 'Organisation', 'North West', 'Manchester, Gorton', 'Greater Manchester', 'Manchester', 18, 'N', 1, '6 weeks', 5, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Theatre', '#REF!', 'North West', 'ALL FM will work with vulnerable members of the South, East and Central Manchester communities. They will learn how to write plays for radio.  These plays will be performed, acted and produced by the community. They will be broadcast on ALL FM 96.9\n\n'),
