(17153829, '', 'Applicant 534', 1387584, 'Urban Fringe', 18, 10.0, 'No', 'REJECTED', 0, 0, 20, 'Q1', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 0, 'Organisation', 'South East', 'Rochester and Strood', 'Medway', 'Medway', 0, 'Y', 0, '6 weeks', 5, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Visual arts', '#REF!', 'South East', 'Action research to develop URBAN Fringe, an arts programme that combines the concepts of fringe festival and urban fringe to put the disadvantaged edges of our towns and cities at the forefront of place making practice through artistic production based on local distinctiveness, directly supporting Localism and the Big Society.'),
(17155073, '', 'Applicant 535', 16566788, 'Dance R and D : Restriction and Liberation', 18, 5.0, 'No', 'OFFERED', 5, 5, 20, 'Q1', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 1, 'Individual', 'South East', 'Brighton, Kemptown', 'Brighton and Hove', 'Brighton and Hove', 4, 'N', 1, '6 weeks', 5, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Dance', '#REF!', 'South East', '14 day choreographic exploration to develop stylistic approaches and responses to ''restrictions''. It  will generate an original 10 minute choreography for four dancers as a work in progress to be performed at three shatings, provide a daily class for local dancers, workshops for dance artists and workshops for dance teachers.\n\n\n'),
