(17160738, '', 'Applicant 542', 9777448, 'Put on Your Dancing Shoes', 18, 9.0, 'No', 'OFFERED', 9, 9, 19, 'Q1', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 1, 'Organisation', 'West Midlands', 'Wolverhampton South West', 'West Midlands', 'Wolverhampton', 10, 'Y', 1, '6 weeks', 5, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Dance', '#REF!', 'West Midlands', 'Put on Your Dancing Shoes is part of wider project, Everybody Dance Now, commissioned by People Dancing and inspired by 2012. There are two aims to stage four large intergenerational and multi-cultural social dances and to publicly showcase dance work by a range of local community and dance groups. \n\n'),
(17162202, '', 'Applicant 543', 17162200, 'Passing Strange & Wonderful', 18, 9.0, 'No', 'OFFERED', 0, 9, 4, 'Q1', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 1, 'Individual', 'South East', 'Brighton, Pavilion', 'Brighton and Hove', 'Brighton and Hove', 2, 'N', 1, '6 weeks', 7, 0, 0, 'Ot', 'Dance', '#REF!', 'South East', 'This is a digital arts reinterpretation of the Ben Wright duet Passing Strange & Wonderful that aims both to make a new, distinctive response, reconfiguring it for a variety of screens in a wide range of contexts, and to develop a new, innovative approach to reaching and developing new audiences.'),
(17162279, '', 'Applicant 544', 17162277, 'Poems: Salvage / Like Ghosts Caught Falling', 18, 3.0, 'No', 'OFFERED', 3, 3, 19, 'Q1', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 1, 'Individual', 'South West', 'Exeter', 'Devon', 'Exeter', 5, 'N', 1, '6 weeks', 5, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Literature', '#REF!', 'South West', 'I am applying for support with the completion of a poetry collection, ''Salvage / Like Ghosts Caught Falling''. The poems I am still to write fall into three series concentrating on themes of childbirth and motherhood, ecological issues and the natural world, and the paintings and letters of Vincent Van Gogh.'),
(17162482, '', 'Applicant 545', 17162480, 'Artistic Collaboration on ''The Edge''', 19, 4.0, 'No', 'OFFERED', 4, 4, 19, 'Q1', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 1, 'Individual', 'London', 'Vauxhall', 'Greater London', 'Lambeth', 28, 'N', 1, '6 weeks', 4, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Theatre', '#REF!', 'London', 'Over 2011, I plan to work as an artistic collaborator on a new piece of theatre, The Edge. The work will be undertaken with Transport Theatre Company, Folkestone and Ranan Performance Collective, Kolkata. It will explore the relationship between climate change and migration.'),
