(17220300, '', 'Applicant 632', 17220298, 'A Return to the Coast', 24, 2.0, 'No', 'OFFERED', 2, 2, 3, 'Q1', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 1, 'Individual', 'Yorkshire and The Humber', 'Beverley and Holderness', 'East Riding of Yorkshire', 'East Riding of Yorkshire', 17, 'N', 1, '6 weeks', 6, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Visual arts', '#REF!', 'Yorkshire', 'Contemporary paintings of the rocks of the Yorkshire coast, exploring the structural language of the rock through the visual language of paint and ink.  Presented in poster form along the length of the Hull-Scarborough railway line, the project revisits the historic link between fine art and the railways.'),
