(17282431, '', 'Applicant 779', 17008257, 'POETRY IN MIND-Poetry Competition for MentalHealth', 4, 7.0, 'Yes', 'REJECTED', 0, 0, 8, 'Q1', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 0, 'Individual', 'South East', 'Horsham', 'West Sussex', 'Horsham', 0, 'Y', 0, '6 weeks', 1, 1, 1, 'Ot', 'Literature', '#REF!', 'South East', 'What is devised is a Nation-Wide (England to begin with, then potentially to Incl. Wales +Scotland) Poetry and Prose Competition for Mental Health care Patients (in both the Private+Nhs Sectors, both Outpatients and In-patients). Entrants will be asked to write Poetry about their experiences with Mental Healthcare.'),
(17282549, '', 'Applicant 780', 14372022, 'The Seagull Effect', 30, 9.0, 'No', 'OFFERED', 9, 9, 11, 'Q1', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 1, 'Organisation', 'South East', 'Oxford West and Abingdon', 'Oxfordshire', 'Oxford', 13, 'N', 1, '6 weeks', 6, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Theatre', '#REF!', 'South East', 'Research and Development wages for 3 weeks for a new piece of multimedia devised physical theatre, The Seagull Effect, exploring the 1987 storm. We want to build on the devising skills we''ve learnt before by integrating video projection into the piece and working with a dramaturg.'),
