(17379789, '', 'Applicant 948', 1618982, 'A River Runs Through It.', 13, 33.0, 'No', 'OFFERED', 33, 33, 12, 'Q2', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 1, 'Organisation', 'North West', 'Westmorland and Lonsdale', 'Cumbria', 'South Lakeland', 2, 'N', 1, '12 weeks', 13, 0, 0, 'Ot', 'Combined arts', '#REF!', 'North West', 'Waterpowered Mills of South Westmorland (1930) by John Somervell inspires this art project that will examine and explore the symbiosis of the water course and mills, within the agricultural landscape. Demographic and rural cyclic change will be observed and represented through Installation, exhibition, performance and bookarts to celebrate the outcomes.'),
