(17478898, '', 'Applicant 1189', 12707021, 'Knot Knitting /Shed Load', 28, 8.0, 'No', 'REJECTED', 0, 0, 6, 'Q1', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 0, 'Organisation', 'East Midlands', 'Northampton South', 'Northamptonshire', 'Northampton', 0, 'N', 0, '6 weeks', 6, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Visual arts', '#REF!', 'East Midlands', 'A series of arts workshops in public spaces (including the Market Square) creating a learning synergy where individuals and groups have opportunities to access arts and to encourage learning and engagement with the arts at neighbourhood level.  Making art as an individual that contributes towards a larger artwork.'),
(17478973, '', 'Applicant 1190', 17478966, 'Projection of single digital images & audio visual', 2, 5.0, 'Yes', 'REJECTED', 0, 0, 13, 'Q1', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 0, 'Organisation', 'South East', 'Tonbridge and Malling', 'Kent', 'Tonbridge and Malling', 0, 'N', 0, '6 weeks', 2, 1, 1, 'Ot', 'Visual arts', '#REF!', 'South East', 'The grant is being sought to purchase and operate, including appropriate software, equipment for the projection of digitally created images / photos to club members during competition and instructional days / club evenings. It will also be used by visiting lecturers and photography judges.'),
(17479034, '', 'Applicant 1191', 17479032, 'Who Do You Think You Are?', 3, 3.0, 'Yes', 'REJECTED', 0, 0, 13, 'Q1', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 0, 'Individual', 'Yorkshire and The Humber', 'Thirsk and Malton', 'North Yorkshire', 'Hambleton', 0, 'N', 0, '6 weeks', 1, 1, 1, 'Ot', 'Literature', '#REF!', 'Yorkshire', 'I am applying for funds to cover childcare in order to give me time to complete my second novel, ''Who Do You Think You Are?'''),
(17479169, '', 'Applicant 1192', 17479162, 'The SuperCollider Symposium 2012', 3, 7.0, 'No', 'REJECTED', 0, 0, 15, 'Q1', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 0, 'Organisation', 'London', 'Chingford and Woodford Green', 'Greater London', 'Redbridge', 0, 'N', 0, '6 weeks', 6, 0, 0, 'Ot', 'Music', '#REF!', 'London', 'We are organising a digital music conference/festival held across multiple venues in London. The focus is SuperCollider, the free and open-source digital audio software, used by musicians and sonic artists worldwide. The Symposium is a cross-disciplinary event, featuring concerts in many artistic styles, installations, and a conference.'),
(17479272, '', 'Applicant 1193', 1625105, 'CINECITY''s  Artists'' Moving Image Programme', 28, 50.0, 'No', 'OFFERED', 50, 50, 12, 'Q2', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 1, 'Organisation', 'South East', 'Brighton, Kemptown', 'Brighton and Hove', 'Brighton and Hove', 2, 'N', 1, '12 weeks', 11, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Visual arts', '#REF!', 'South East', 'We are seeking support to present CINECITY''s artists'' moving image programmes in 2011 & 2012, develop our organisational capacity and implement our digital strategy.'),
(17479387, '', 'Applicant 1194', 17479379, 'Bridgtown 100 years celebration.', 28, 2.0, 'Yes', 'REJECTED', 0, 0, 11, 'Q1', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 0, 'Organisation', 'West Midlands', 'Cannock Chase', 'Staffordshire', 'Cannock Chase', 0, 'N', 0, '6 weeks', 2, 1, 1, 'Ot', 'Visual arts', '#REF!', 'West Midlands', 'Children of primary age of all abilities will work with an artist in residence to produce a mosaic art piece that represents the local area. Local community history society and wider community will be involved. The mosaic will be a lasting monument to celebrate Bridgtown past and present.'),
(17479451, '', 'Applicant 1195', 17479444, 'Hollydale Community Carnival', 28, 3.0, 'No', 'REJECTED', 0, 0, 7, 'Q1', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 0, 'Organisation', 'London', 'Camberwell and Peckham', 'Greater London', 'Southwark', 0, 'N', 0, '6 weeks', 6, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Combined arts', '#REF!', 'London', 'Hollydale school would like to organize a Carnival in place of our biannual international evening.  We would like to use this as a means of developing cross curricular themes within the school as well as strengthening links with local community groups and  the wider community in which the school stands.'),
(17479577, '', 'Applicant 1196', 17479570, 'Wide Awake Devon 12 Month Programme', 2, 37.0, 'No', 'OFFERED', 37, 37, 13, 'Q2', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 1, 'Organisation', 'South West', 'Exeter', 'Devon', 'Exeter', 9, 'N', 1, '12 weeks', 10, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Theatre', '#REF!', 'South West', 'We create opportunities for the live performance community to develop face to face relationships, allowing them to share ideas, knowledge, resources and issues with each other. Our projects will provide opportunities to devise creative ways to make, produce and promote new work in a productive and collaborative environment.'),
(17479799, '', 'Applicant 1197', 1623479, 'Living Local Traditions & the Stations of the Sun', 3, 9.0, 'No', 'OFFERED', 9, 9, 8, 'Q1', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 1, 'Organisation', 'South East', 'Henley', 'Oxfordshire', 'South Oxfordshire', 16, 'Y', 1, '6 weeks', 5, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Music', '#REF!', 'South East', '4 artists explore local folk music and traditional festivals with 60 school children in West Berkshire, learning folk instruments and co-creating new music for local performances. Local source material collected will then features in the development of professional touring show based on our forgotten festive cycle (12 public performances)'),
