(17485843, '', 'Applicant 1206', 1599982, 'Organisational Development for Coney 2011', 2, 45.0, 'No', 'OFFERED', 45, 45, 13, 'Q2', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 1, 'Organisation', 'London', 'Hackney South and Shoreditch', 'Greater London', 'Hackney', 9, 'N', 1, '12 weeks', 10, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Theatre', '#REF!', 'London', 'Coney needs to develop its infrastructure in order to best capitalise on  the National Portfolio award which will commence in April 2012. This will look at staff and governance structure, financial sustainability and how best to support its work on tour.'),
(17486954, '', 'Applicant 1207', 6532588, 'Walking to Hades  (working title)', 3, 2.0, 'No', 'REJECTED', 0, 0, 8, 'Q1', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 0, 'Individual', 'South East', 'Dover', 'Kent', 'Dover', 0, 'N', 0, '6 weeks', 5, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Combined arts', '#REF!', 'South East', 'This project involves a walk, story-gathering, photography, creative archaeology and public participation. It centres on a walk linking two seaside towns of Deal and Margate, both key in the artist''s childhood, and revisited as an adult in a pilgrimage in search not of Heaven, but Hades...'),
(17488000, '', 'Applicant 1208', 1637428, 'Internal relocation of Gallery', 3, 60.0, 'Yes', 'REJECTED', 0, 0, 12, 'Q1', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 0, 'Organisation', 'Yorkshire and The Humber', 'Calder Valley', 'West Yorkshire', 'Calderdale', 0, 'N', 0, '12 weeks', 1, 1, 1, 'Ot', 'Visual arts', '#REF!', 'Yorkshire', 'We are moving our gallery space from the top floor of Linden Mill to the bottom floor enabling us to improve our access and facilities.'),
(17488082, '', 'Applicant 1209', 17488076, 'Henry the Eighth ballons released at York Minster', 3, 1.0, 'Yes', 'REJECTED', 0, 0, 11, 'Q1', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 0, 'Individual', 'East Midlands', 'Bassetlaw', 'Nottinghamshire', 'Bassetlaw', 0, 'N', 0, '6 weeks', 1, 1, 1, 'Ot', 'Combined arts', '#REF!', 'East Midlands', 'To involve dance groups in York in a procession to release 500 Henry the Eighth Balloons over York minster. Involving the public in a joyfull reliese of patriarchal grudges and to perform  two songs I have written one at the begining of the event and one at the end.'),
(17488144, '', 'Applicant 1210', 14363340, 'Artistic and Audience development at Mostly Jazz', 3, 8.0, 'No', 'OFFERED', 8, 8, 8, 'Q1', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 1, 'Organisation', 'West Midlands', 'Birmingham, Ladywood', 'West Midlands', 'Birmingham', 13, 'Y', 1, '6 weeks', 5, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Combined arts', '#REF!', 'West Midlands', 'The Mostly Jazz Festival is in its second year. In addition to our two main stages we also have a third stage for which we are proposing a programme of spoken word and jazz poetry, music making and dance workshops, artist discussion and additional performance opportunity for emergent artists. \n'),
(17489303, '', 'Applicant 1211', 9398146, 'Durham Oriental Museum Interactive Table', 3, 8.0, 'No', 'OFFERED', 8, 8, 7, 'Q1', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 1, 'Individual', 'North East', 'City of Durham', 'Durham', 'County Durham', 20, 'N', 1, '6 weeks', 5, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Visual arts', '#REF!', 'North East', 'The activity will be to create an interactive table artwork to work alongside the Chinese ceramic collection from the Oriental Museum, Durham. Interactive images will be projected onto objects on the table. The artwork will be initially hosted at the Oriental Museum with potential to be sited at Palace Green.'),
(17489378, '', 'Applicant 1212', 1815609, 'Wasanii International Artists'' Workshop', 3, 1.0, 'No', 'OFFERED', 1, 1, 7, 'Q1', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 1, 'Individual', 'North West', 'Liverpool, Riverside', 'Merseyside', 'Liverpool', 14, 'N', 1, '6 weeks', 5, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Visual arts', '#REF!', 'North West', 'Visit to Kuona Trust art centre in Nairobi and participation in Wasanii International Artists'),
(17489475, '', 'Applicant 1213', 1845384, 'Production of Goodbye Barcelona at Arcola Theatre', 3, 27.0, 'No', 'OFFERED', 27, 27, 13, 'Q2', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 1, 'Individual', 'London', 'Bethnal Green and Bow', 'Greater London', 'Tower Hamlets', 1, 'N', 1, '12 weeks', 10, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Theatre', '#REF!', 'London', 'We are Judith Johnson (playwright)  and Karl Lewkowicz (composer/lyricist).  We are mounting a production of our musical, Goodbye Barcelona, at Arcola Theatre November/December 2011. We are applying for a contribution towards production costs.  This professional production of our show will help our progression as a musical writing partnership. \n'),
(17489561, '', 'Applicant 1214', 17489559, 'Making Theatre: Gaining Skills', 3, 6.0, 'No', 'OFFERED', 6, 6, 8, 'Q1', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 1, 'Individual', 'South East', 'Havant', 'Hampshire', 'Havant', 16, 'N', 1, '6 weeks', 5, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Theatre', '#REF!', 'South East', 'A unique learning programme for young people providing practical experience of technical, administrative and production roles combined with embedded delivery of key skills in literacy, numeracy and ICT.  The two-week intensive programme can be delivered in a range of settings and offered as bespoke pre-apprenticeship courses.'),
(17489653, '', 'Applicant 1215', 1862240, 'Screening Room / Chronomter', 3, 9.0, 'No', 'OFFERED', 9, 9, 8, 'Q1', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 1, 'Individual', 'Yorkshire and The Humber', 'Leeds North West', 'West Yorkshire', 'Leeds', 8, 'N', 1, '6 weeks', 5, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Visual arts', '#REF!', 'Yorkshire', 'Support towards the development and delivery of two distinct but interrelated projects: ''Chronometer,'' a major new book of the collected writings of artist Ken Jacobs; and ''Screening Room'' a new commission and artwork that I intend to produce collaboratively with artist Paul Rooney for presentation at the 2012 AV Festival.'),
(17489748, '', 'Applicant 1216', 17489746, 'Noir Machine (working title)', 3, 9.0, 'No', 'REJECTED', 0, 0, 7, 'Q1', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 0, 'Individual', 'London', 'Islington South and Finsbury', 'Greater London', 'Islington', 0, 'N', 0, '6 weeks', 5, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Dance', '#REF!', 'London', 'This is a proposal to develop and produce a piece of dance theatre that applies the aesthetic and psychological elements of film noir to our own dark city, London in 2011. It combines original choreography and music to tell a story of individual and socio-economic change.'),
(17489838, '', 'Applicant 1217', 1840029, '''Roaming''', 3, 39.0, 'No', 'OFFERED', 39, 39, 12, 'Q2', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 1, 'Individual', 'Eastern', 'Cambridge', 'Cambridgeshire', 'Cambridge', 6, 'N', 1, '12 weeks', 10, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Visual arts', '#REF!', 'East', '''Roaming'' is the first major project undertaken by ROAM, an artist-led group formed through Escalator Visual Arts.   ''Roaming'' will explore and create new work inspired by encounters, the folklore of the region and boundaries realised as a series site-specific actions, happenings and events across the East of England.'),
(17489948, '', 'Applicant 1218', 17489946, 'Eternal Torment Productions', 3, 19.0, 'Yes', 'REJECTED', 0, 0, 9, 'Q1', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 0, 'Individual', 'London', 'Lewisham, Deptford', 'Greater London', 'Lewisham', 0, 'Y', 0, '12 weeks', 1, 1, 1, 'Ot', 'Theatre', '#REF!', 'London', 'We will build scare mazes which are very interactive and more theatrical than a simple scary walkthrough with jump scares. We will have no fixed abode which will allow us to travel and build around the country. We will include work with children and schools.'),
(17490005, '', 'Applicant 1219', 17490003, 'Show at london fashion week', 4, 3.0, 'Yes', 'REJECTED', 0, 0, 10, 'Q1', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 0, 'Individual', 'London', 'Brent North', 'Greater London', 'Brent', 0, 'N', 0, '6 weeks', 1, 1, 1, 'Ot', 'Visual arts', '#REF!', 'London', 'I am an upcoming young designer. Having only graduated in July i have received lots of positive feedback about my work and have the opportunity to show at london fashion week in september but am struggling with finding the funds to produce the new collection.'),
(17492819, '', 'Applicant 1220', 1601113, 'Literary translation workshop programme', 4, 7.0, 'No', 'REJECTED', 0, 0, 7, 'Q1', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 0, 'Organisation', 'London', 'Chelsea and Fulham', 'Greater London', 'Kensington and Chelsea', 0, 'Y', 0, '6 weeks', 5, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Literature', '#REF!', 'London', 'Following the success of the workshops we have run in recent years, we are planning to work in partnership with The Reading Agency to develop a series of workshops that will reach out to new audiences spread across the UK, as well as to practising and trainee translators.'),
(17492887, '', 'Applicant 1221', 12084236, 'Chi-TEK', 4, 10.0, 'No', 'OFFERED', 10, 10, 7, 'Q1', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 1, 'Organisation', 'London', 'Bermondsey and Old Southwark', 'Greater London', 'Southwark', 5, 'N', 1, '6 weeks', 5, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Visual arts', '#REF!', 'London', 'Chi-TEK  is an exciting womans creative technology project, encompassing a three month showcase of newly commissioned artwork at the Victoria & Albert Sackler Centre, a workshop series, and a weekend event in the Victoria & Albert Museums Gardens, coinciding with the Crafts Council ''Power of Making'' and V&A Digital Weekend.  \n\n'),
(17494182, '', 'Applicant 1222', 1586297, 'Community Arts', 4, 1.0, 'Yes', 'REJECTED', 0, 0, 10, 'Q1', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 0, 'Organisation', 'South East', 'Oxford East', 'Oxfordshire', 'Oxford', 0, 'Y', 0, '6 weeks', 1, 1, 1, 'Ot', 'Visual arts', '#REF!', 'South East', 'Our Art project involves work with adults with learning disabilities, it is a community based project run away from the centre which aims to get the group involved within the wider community, encouraging integration while raising disability awareness among local residents'),
(17494286, '', 'Applicant 1223', 10092126, 'Creation of three new works', 4, 6.0, 'No', 'REJECTED', 0, 0, 7, 'Q1', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 0, 'Individual', 'Yorkshire and The Humber', 'Sheffield Central', 'South Yorkshire', 'Sheffield', 0, 'N', 0, '6 weeks', 5, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Visual arts', '#REF!', 'Yorkshire', 'I want to realise a series of three new interrelated video works which will rely on robust collaborations with actors and technicians and which will explore further pivotal themes within my practice. Once realised, I want to exhibit these works in new and progressive ways.');
