(18340202, '', 'Applicant 2925', 18340200, 'Residency at The Burren Art College & UK Shows', 11, 2.0, 'No', 'OFFERED', 2, 2, 20, 'Q2', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 1, 'Individual', 'London', 'Islington South and Finsbury', 'Greater London', 'Islington', 28, 'N', 1, '6 weeks', 6, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Visual arts', '#REF!', 'London', 'This residency will allow me to complete a body of photographic work in preparation for a solo show and a group show both of which will take place in London in early 2012. As well as studio space, I will have access to workshops, lectures, darkrooms and photographic studios.'),
(18340274, '', 'Applicant 2926', 18340272, 'Faith in the Potteries', 11, 15.0, 'No', 'OFFERED', 15, 15, 2, 'Q3', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 1, 'Individual', 'West Midlands', 'Stone', 'Staffordshire', 'Stafford', 11, 'Y', 1, '12 weeks', 12, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Visual arts', '#REF!', 'West Midlands', 'A photographic exhibition based around the multi-faiths in the region celebrating the cultural diversity and ethnicity of the people of the Potteries. The exhibition will be a working exhibit to allow community input, involvement and comment. The Location is in the industrial Spode Site factory in Stoke on Trent.'),
(18341326, '', 'Applicant 2927', 6279668, '''Penumbra''', 11, 10.0, 'No', 'OFFERED', 10, 10, 22, 'Q2', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 1, 'Organisation', 'Eastern', 'South Cambridgeshire', 'Cambridgeshire', 'South Cambridgeshire', 4, 'N', 1, '6 weeks', 6, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Theatre', '#REF!', 'East', 'We intend to research and develop our second theatre piece for adults, leading to showings at the Suspense Festival November 2011 and Gulbenkian Theatre, Canterbury. ''Penumbra'' will involve an innovative exploration of the human body, using live animation of shadows and puppets - on the theme of desire and decay.'),
