(18409164, '', 'Applicant 3086', 14875871, 'The International Literary Quarterly', 21, 20.0, 'No', 'REJECTED', 0, 0, 1, 'Q3', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 0, 'Individual', 'London', 'Leyton and Wanstead', 'Greater London', 'Waltham Forest', 0, 'N', 0, '12 weeks', 10, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Literature', '#REF!', 'London', 'The International Literary Quarterly" (aka Interlitq) is an on-line literary publication that seeks to nurture and disseminate high-quality international literature, and that has, to date, published literature in more than 90 languages. Its overriding objective is to showcase the multi-ethnic and multi-cultural component of literature.\n\n'),
