(18455382, '', 'Applicant 3176', 1845804, 'Kitty Lake''s Journey to the Outer Hebrides in 1931', 26, 6.0, 'No', 'REJECTED', 6, 0, 4, 'Q3', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 0, 'Individual', 'London', 'Islington North', 'Greater London', 'Islington', 0, 'N', 0, '6 weeks', 6, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Visual arts', '#REF!', 'London', 'The project will take place in the Outer Hebrides in Scotland, retracing the journey Kitty Lake, the anthropologist made in 1931 exploring the local weaving community . The second part will be an installation entitled ''The Weaving Shed'' set up in an empty shop in The High Street, Stroud, Gloucestershire.'),
