(18530586, '', 'Applicant 3333', 1851582, '11 11 11 - in remembrance - Manchester', 9, 5.0, 'No', 'OFFERED', 5, 5, 18, 'Q3', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 1, 'Individual', 'North West', 'Manchester Central', 'Greater Manchester', 'Manchester', 31, 'N', 1, '6 weeks', 6, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Visual arts', '#REF!', 'North West', 'A one-off live/performance art event on 11.11.11.\nOn the 11th hour of the 11th month in the 11th year of the 21st Century, 11 artists perform 11 new performances that are all specific to the day, the event and the site.\nLocation: Platt Chapel'),
(18531314, '', 'Applicant 3334', 1386855, 'World Poems on the Underground', 9, 33.0, 'No', 'OFFERED', 33, 33, 29, 'Q3', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 1, 'Organisation', 'London', 'Holborn and St Pancras', 'Greater London', 'Camden', 8, 'Y', 1, '12 weeks', 12, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Literature', '#REF!', 'London', 'A 48-page DL booklet of poems from each continent, drawn from our international sets, with six new international poems to be featured in Feb/Mar 2012, 120,000 copies free at Tube stations and libraries, celebrating contemporary poets worldwide as well as London'),
(18531416, '', 'Applicant 3335', 1842375, 'Be Like Water', 9, 9.0, 'No', 'OFFERED', 9, 9, 18, 'Q3', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 1, 'Individual', 'East Midlands', 'Nottingham North', 'Nottingham', 'Nottingham', 31, 'Y', 1, '6 weeks', 6, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Theatre', '#REF!', 'East Midlands', 'Research and development for a new theatrical live performance by cross-disciplinary artist Hetain Patel. Primarily working in a studio with a team of  artistic collaborators. Culminating in a free public presentation at New Art Exchange, Nottingham, at which future potential investors will be present, including Royal Opera House, London.'),
(18532028, '', 'Applicant 3336', 14197721, 'Cheltenham Poetry Festival', 9, 7.0, 'No', 'OFFERED', 7, 7, 25, 'Q3', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 1, 'Individual', 'South West', 'Cheltenham', 'Gloucestershire', 'Cheltenham', 4, 'Y', 1, '6 weeks', 7, 0, 0, 'Ot', 'Literature', '#REF!', 'South West', 'I would like to expand on the outreach programme for Cheltenham Poetry Festival. \nThe festival will include free workshops, readings, film showings and live music. \nThe festival will offer events targeted at the poorer wards of the town and at those with physical barriers to cultural inclusion.  \n'),
(18532480, '', 'Applicant 3337', 4471997, 'Kent Youth Arts Development Programme', 9, 10.0, 'No', 'OFFERED', 10, 10, 19, 'Q3', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 1, 'Organisation', 'South East', 'Maidstone and The Weald', 'Kent', 'Maidstone', 25, 'Y', 1, '6 weeks', 6, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Combined arts', '#REF!', 'South East', 'KADU will deliver a development programme of local and regional significance, providing support, activity and opportunities in youth arts across the county. Including Youth Arts Festival in partnership with Turner Contemporary, Youth Arts Production Company, Young Arts Ambassadors, Youth Arts Network and progression routes for young people and artists.'),
(18532589, '', 'Applicant 3338', 14166246, 'The Lonely Clouds of Guernica', 9, 8.0, 'No', 'OFFERED', 8, 8, 18, 'Q3', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 1, 'Individual', 'North West', 'Manchester Central', 'Greater Manchester', 'Manchester', 24, 'Y', 1, '6 weeks', 6, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Theatre', '#REF!', 'North West', 'A soldier returns from Afghanistan with no idea how to re-start his life or rejoin society. His sister insists he go into therapy for his post-traumatic stress disorder. But he''ll have to survive his nightmares if he''s to survive at all.'),
(18532774, '', 'Applicant 3339', 18532772, 'The Art of Sport', 9, 7.0, 'No', 'REJECTED', 0, 0, 20, 'Q3', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 0, 'Individual', 'London', 'Twickenham', 'Greater London', 'Richmond upon Thames', 0, 'Y', 0, '6 weeks', 6, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Visual arts', '#REF!', 'London', 'The activity will use art to observe sporting activities and explore the potential for cross curricular learning for education groups in school and community settings. The aim is to document this through a Big Draw Event, which will act as a springboard for launching a national learning pack.'),
(18532866, '', 'Applicant 3340', 15415960, 'Pandora''s Box', 9, 45.0, 'No', 'OFFERED', 45, 45, 29, 'Q3', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 1, 'Individual', 'London', 'Hackney North and Stoke Newington', 'Greater London', 'Hackney', 12, 'N', 1, '12 weeks', 12, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Theatre', '#REF!', 'London', '''Pandora''s Box '' is a full production of  an original, contemporary new play by Nigerian-British playwright Ade Solanke, to be staged at the Albany Empire, London from Feb 27th - March 16th 2012. This production  harnesses significant media exposure, audience  interest and  economic and creative investment  achieved earlier this year.\n'),
(18533017, '', 'Applicant 3341', 14806908, 'Breathing Space Art & wellbeing with at-risk youth', 9, 49.0, 'No', 'OFFERED', 49, 49, 29, 'Q3', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 1, 'Individual', 'Yorkshire and The Humber', 'Leeds North West', 'West Yorkshire', 'Leeds', 23, 'N', 1, '12 weeks', 12, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Visual arts', '#REF!', 'Yorkshire', 'New-media/digital/photographic art will provide two years engagement and stability for at-risk young people. A unique partnership passionate about benefits of art and wellbeing to affect change boasts a strong arts rationale; providing future opportunities, including the Arts Award, whilst supporting current agendas and individuals artistic ambitions.'),
(18533832, '', 'Applicant 3342', 15724011, '''Pete  Verses Climate Change!''  Development', 9, 7.0, 'No', 'OFFERED', 7, 7, 19, 'Q3', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 1, 'Individual', 'South East', 'Oxford East', 'Oxfordshire', 'Oxford', 23, 'N', 1, '6 weeks', 6, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Literature', '#REF!', 'South East', 'A revised application to develop a spoken word stage show about climate change following extensive professional consultation and audience feedback. Having sourced the right external support I seek to make the changes and carry out showcases over three nights in two different locations in preparation for a successful national tour. \n'),
