(18537101, '', 'Applicant 3355', 1605239, 'Production of ''The Oresteia'' by Aeschylus', 10, 34.0, 'No', 'OFFERED', 34, 34, 29, 'Q3', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 1, 'Organisation', 'London', 'Ealing Central and Acton', 'Greater London', 'Ealing', 21, 'Y', 1, '12 weeks', 11, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Theatre', '#REF!', 'London', '''The Oresteia''  charts events following Agamemnon''s return from the Trojan War. It embodies societies most savage crimes, and takes us from a savage society where justice can only be achieved through vengeance to a civilised society that uses reason to judge society''s ills.'),
