(18571724, '', 'Applicant 3413', 1602512, 'Phenomenal People', 14, 34.0, 'No', 'OFFERED', 34, 34, 29, 'Q3', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 1, 'Organisation', 'London', 'Battersea', 'Greater London', 'Wandsworth', 14, 'N', 1, '12 weeks', 11, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Theatre', '#REF!', 'London', 'Phenomenal People will be a live and digital artwork celebrating inspiring women. It will be a new performing arts project created by Fuel to celebrate inspirational women, in a playful and interactive way.'),
(18572263, '', 'Applicant 3414', 1388376, 'Access Space Sustainability Project (ASSP)', 14, 44.0, 'No', 'OFFERED', 44, 44, 29, 'Q3', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 1, 'Organisation', 'Yorkshire and The Humber', 'Sheffield Central', 'South Yorkshire', 'Sheffield', 23, 'N', 1, '12 weeks', 11, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Visual arts', '#REF!', 'Yorkshire', 'Access Space Sustainability Project  is an arts project designed to strengthen Access Space through enhancing its core activity. \nIt will increase our reach locally, create opportunities for emerging and mid career artists, explore new income streams and develop a new international context for Access Space through DIY FabLab Artist Residencies\n'),
(18572338, '', 'Applicant 3415', 10629148, 'Trinity manchester', 14, 7.0, 'No', 'REJECTED', 7, 0, 18, 'Q3', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 0, 'Individual', 'North West', 'Ellesmere Port and Neston', 'Cheshire', 'Cheshire West and Chester', 0, 'N', 0, '6 weeks', 5, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Visual arts', '#REF!', 'North West', 'Trinity is a public art intervention that uses three digital mirrors (plasma screen and video camera) placed for several weeks at separate locations within Piccadilly train station, Manchester.\nWe want to pull passers by from their journey'),
(18572437, '', 'Applicant 3416', 1851753, 'Reykjavik 2010, Detroit 2011, Liverpool 2012', 14, 1.0, 'No', 'REJECTED', 0, 0, 18, 'Q3', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 0, 'Individual', 'North West', 'Garston and Halewood', 'Merseyside', 'Liverpool', 0, 'Y', 0, '6 weeks', 5, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Visual arts', '#REF!', 'North West', 'I am invited to perform a live artwork in Detroit in November, exhibiting with artists I met on my residency in Iceland 2010. Expanding the Iceland/Detroit link, I plan to bring the exchange to Liverpool, with their similar cultural/musical heritages- to show with artists here in 2012 Biennial.'),
(18572522, '', 'Applicant 3417', 6425193, 'Knight Watch & Black T-shirt Collection', 14, 49.0, 'No', 'OFFERED', 49, 49, 23, 'Q3', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', 'National activities', 1, 'Individual', 'London', 'Battersea', 'Greater London', 'Wandsworth', 1, 'Y', 1, '12 weeks', 10, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Theatre', '#REF!', 'London', 'Inua Ellams is seeking funding to develop and tour two new projects: Black T-shirt Collection and Knight Watch. Both projects will be produced by Fuel.'),
(18572643, '', 'Applicant 3418', 1388265, 'Coastival''s Rather Splendid Day Out', 15, 10.0, 'No', 'OFFERED', 10, 10, 25, 'Q3', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 1, 'Organisation', 'Yorkshire and The Humber', 'Scarborough and Whitby', 'North Yorkshire', 'Scarborough', 4, 'Y', 1, '6 weeks', 6, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Combined arts', '#REF!', 'Yorkshire', 'Create is going to organise a one day Coastival event on 11th February 2012.  This is to enable Coastival to enter into and have a presence within the 2012 celebrations.  The event will include performances, exhibitions, and workshops at a number of venues in Scarborough.'),
(18573321, '', 'Applicant 3419', 12458242, 'Malaria Triptych', 15, 8.0, 'No', 'OFFERED', 8, 8, 25, 'Q3', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 1, 'Individual', 'South West', 'East Devon', 'Devon', 'Exeter', 22, 'N', 1, '6 weeks', 6, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Visual arts', '#REF!', 'South West', 'This is a collaboration between artist Deborah Robinson and scientists at the Wellcome Trust Sanger Institute in the creation of an experimental digital artwork that explores cutting edge research into malaria. Alongside we will produce a short film documenting exchange between collaborators as the artwork develops.\n\n'),
(18575315, '', 'Applicant 3420', 18575313, 'Resolutions', 15, 7.0, 'No', 'REJECTED', 0, 0, 26, 'Q3', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 0, 'Individual', 'South East', 'Buckingham', 'Buckinghamshire', 'Aylesbury Vale', 0, 'N', 0, '6 weeks', 6, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Dance', '#REF!', 'South East', 'Resolutions is an annual event taking place at The Place. The plarform invites new aspiring choeographers and dance companies to preview their works.The performances are reviewd by emerging and established critics.This has been  a vital stepping stone for some of the most successful choreographers.'),
(18575372, '', 'Applicant 3421', 6532588, 'Back to A Land', 15, 10.0, 'No', 'REJECTED', 10, 0, 26, 'Q3', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 0, 'Individual', 'South East', 'Dover', 'Kent', 'Dover', 0, 'Y', 0, '6 weeks', 6, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Visual arts', '#REF!', 'South East', 'This is a photography based project inspired by the book A Land, written by the archaeologist and poet, Jacquetta Hawkes. I am her biographer and will revisit and photograph places which feature in A Land, giving them a context  60 years later.'),
