(18652444, '', 'Applicant 3614', 18652437, 'Agent 160 presents Agent 160 (parts one and two)', 27, 6.0, 'No', 'OFFERED', 6, 6, 2, 'Q3', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 1, 'Organisation', 'Eastern', 'South Cambridgeshire', 'Cambridgeshire', 'South Cambridgeshire', 14, 'N', 1, '6 weeks', 5, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Theatre', '#REF!', 'East', 'We are seeking part funding for three two-night runs of ''Agent 160 presents Agent 160'' - a show in two parts which will launch a new theatre company run by female playwrights from across the country. In England, this launch will be staged at Theatre 503 on February 19/20.'),
(18652548, '', 'Applicant 3615', 15615073, 'Bloomin''Arts training day', 27, 9.0, 'No', 'REJECTED', 0, 0, 2, 'Q3', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 0, 'Organisation', 'South East', 'East Surrey', 'Surrey', 'Tandridge', 0, 'N', 0, '6 weeks', 5, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Combined arts', '#REF!', 'South East', 'This is a two year project which aims to take 10 to 15 individuals with learning disabilities  and training them in art , dance and drama in order to deliver an interactive production and Arts workshop for elderly people in the East Surrey area.'),
(18652614, '', 'Applicant 3616', 18652612, 'Devised Piece of Theatre', 27, 3.0, 'Yes', 'REJECTED', 0, 0, 6, 'Q3', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 0, 'Individual', 'London', 'Hendon', 'Greater London', 'Barnet', 0, 'N', 0, '6 weeks', 1, 1, 1, 'Ot', 'Theatre', '#REF!', 'London', 'Our activity is a piece of devised theatre that we are hoping to take to the Edinburgh Fringe Festival in 2012.  It will be based on a short piece of work we produced a couple of years ago called ''Projections'' that evaluates whether we communicate truthfully to each other.'),
(18653663, '', 'Applicant 3617', 18653656, 'Art in the community', 27, 1.0, 'Yes', 'REJECTED', 0, 0, 6, 'Q3', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 0, 'Organisation', 'East Midlands', 'Ashfield', 'Nottinghamshire', 'Ashfield', 0, 'N', 0, '6 weeks', 1, 1, 1, 'Ot', 'Visual arts', '#REF!', 'East Midlands', 'Support of an arts group in Selston, an ex mining area in Nottinghamshire. The arts group runs weekly and consists primarily of retired people, many of whom are faced with rural isolation.  The primary form of art is painting, and exhibitions are held to share the work with the community.'),
(18653728, '', 'Applicant 3618', 18547102, 'Routes & Rhythm - The Journey of the Drum', 12, 5.0, 'No', 'REJECTED', 5, 0, 5, 'Q3', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 0, 'Organisation', 'South East', 'Wycombe', 'Buckinghamshire', 'Wycombe', 0, 'Y', 0, '6 weeks', 3, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Combined arts', '#REF!', 'South East', '350 people from the local community will bring to life `Routes & Rhythm - `The Journey Of The Drum'', from Africa to Brazil, combined with elegant vocal styles of South African and African-American music and dance.  The performance will provide a deeper insight into the routes of African music & dance.'),
(18655014, '', 'Applicant 3619', 18103952, 'Sparklers dance/drama group', 27, 4.0, 'No', 'REJECTED', 0, 0, 1, 'Q3', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 0, 'Individual', 'Yorkshire and The Humber', 'Skipton and Ripon', 'North Yorkshire', 'Craven', 0, 'N', 0, '6 weeks', 5, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Dance', '#REF!', 'Yorkshire', 'This activity works with children/teenagers with autism and special needs and their siblings. It provides a regular dance/ drama session to two groups of young people in the Skipton area and a longer monthly session as a joint group, there is currently no other activity like this on offer.'),
(18656897, '', 'Applicant 3620', 12414672, 'Taboo', 27, 9.0, 'No', 'REJECTED', 9, 0, 1, 'Q3', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 0, 'Individual', 'London', 'Hackney North and Stoke Newington', 'Greater London', 'Hackney', 0, 'N', 0, '6 weeks', 5, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Theatre', '#REF!', 'London', 'R&D to create material for  a full length solo theatre clown show for adults exploring and challenging religion, politics and other taboos as a starting point. The show is going to be devised, highly visual, and physical, with only little text, with the long-term aim of touring.'),
(18657019, '', 'Applicant 3621', 13891472, 'Portrait of an Athlete', 27, 24.0, 'No', 'REJECTED', 24, 0, 14, 'Q3', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 0, 'Organisation', 'North West', 'Salford and Eccles', 'Greater Manchester', 'Salford', 0, 'Y', 0, '12 weeks', 11, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Visual arts', '#REF!', 'North West', 'Creating a series of short artist films that explore the relationship of visiting international Olympic and paralympic athletes with their host training camps in the northwest. The focus is on the cultural experience of the athlete and our creative response to these situations as artists and film-makers.'),
(18657112, '', 'Applicant 3622', 18657110, 'A Wobbly History of Opera - A show for families', 28, 7.0, 'No', 'REJECTED', 7, 0, 1, 'Q3', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 0, 'Individual', 'London', 'Islington North', 'Greater London', 'Islington', 0, 'Y', 0, '6 weeks', 5, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Music', '#REF!', 'London', 'To develop a new show for families by established improvised opera troupe Impropera taking a hilarious romp through the history of opera and classical music styles. The project includes R+D time for the company to develop new skills and two performances at the Kings Place Festival.'),
