(18664055, '', 'Applicant 3631', 1840627, 'R&D for Clarity [cube space project]', 28, 9.0, 'No', 'OFFERED', 9, 9, 2, 'Q3', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 1, 'Individual', 'Eastern', 'Braintree', 'Essex', 'Braintree', 16, 'Y', 1, '6 weeks', 5, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Dance', '#REF!', 'East', 'I want to research new projection techniques and methodologies and to explore how these can be integrated into my live choreographic work as I develop towards the creation of a new work.\n'),
(18665140, '', 'Applicant 3632', 18665134, 'Other World Photography Exhibition', 28, 5.0, 'Yes', 'REJECTED', 0, 0, 6, 'Q3', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 0, 'Individual', 'London', 'Poplar and Limehouse', 'Greater London', 'Tower Hamlets', 0, 'N', 0, '6 weeks', 1, 1, 1, 'Ot', 'Visual arts', '#REF!', 'London', 'The activity is a photography project about mental health issues concentrating in psychosis.'),
(18667008, '', 'Applicant 3633', 1848314, 'NDust', 28, 9.0, 'No', 'OFFERED', 9, 9, 1, 'Q3', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 1, 'Individual', 'London', 'Tottenham', 'Greater London', 'Haringey', 18, 'N', 1, '6 weeks', 5, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Visual arts', '#REF!', 'London', 'NDust is a collaborative project exploring the hidden connections between contemporary industry and ancient myths and rites. Formerly, rites were practiced as a way of communicating with the invisible. Today the greater part of scientific research and industry remains invisible. Outcomes include an installation artwork available for public touring.'),
(18667158, '', 'Applicant 3634', 9737270, 'An Introduction To Art For Disabled People', 28, 18.0, 'No', 'REJECTED', 18, 0, 14, 'Q3', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 0, 'Organisation', 'North West', 'Liverpool, Riverside', 'Merseyside', 'Liverpool', 0, 'N', 0, '12 weeks', 11, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Visual arts', '#REF!', 'North West', 'The main aim of the ten month programme is to provide art training,  through the staging of seven projects, specifically for Merseyside-based disabled people.  They will  each contain a series of workshops, and in one project, also an exhibition of the artwork created.'),
(18667302, '', 'Applicant 3635', 18012712, 'Basta The Second', 28, 4.0, 'No', 'OFFERED', 4, 4, 1, 'Q3', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 1, 'Individual', 'London', 'Holborn and St Pancras', 'Greater London', 'Camden', 15, 'N', 1, '6 weeks', 5, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Literature', '#REF!', 'London', 'I''m a literary writer applying for a grant enabling me to write an experimental novella. My two previous books have been published by non-profit small press 8fold in 2010/2011 respectively, and I have now been commissioned to write a third; http://www.8fold.org/bubka.html'),
(18667430, '', 'Applicant 3636', 1862246, 'Defining Places', 28, 8.0, 'No', 'REJECTED', 0, 0, 1, 'Q3', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 0, 'Individual', 'Yorkshire and The Humber', 'Leeds North West', 'West Yorkshire', 'Leeds', 0, 'N', 0, '6 weeks', 5, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Visual arts', '#REF!', 'Yorkshire', 'I am a visual artist applying for a grant for making new work and professional development. The work will be 8 paintings, the theme - belonging and acceptance in Yorkshire . The aim at the end of this activity is to become a full-time practising artist, encouraging others with ''invisible disabilities''.'),
(18669162, '', 'Applicant 3637', 18669160, 'Differing Realities', 28, 9.0, 'Yes', 'REJECTED', 0, 0, 3, 'Q3', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 0, 'Individual', 'East Midlands', 'Leicester South', 'Leicester', 'Leicester', 0, 'Y', 0, '6 weeks', 1, 1, 1, 'Ot', 'Visual arts', '#REF!', 'East Midlands', 'I will be exploring/filming culture in Thailand. It will be part of a project, where I will also be teaching English in schools and English centres. I will be delivering Drama and performance extra-curriculum activities and hope to participate in Thai cookery, dance, traditional art and Thai boxing.'),
(18669247, '', 'Applicant 3638', 1843906, 'Vocalising Manifestos (working title)', 28, 4.0, 'No', 'OFFERED', 4, 4, 7, 'Q3', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 1, 'Individual', 'London', 'Bermondsey and Old Southwark', 'Greater London', 'Southwark', 16, 'N', 1, '6 weeks', 6, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Combined arts', '#REF!', 'London', 'My activity is to vocalise manifestos from the Womens Art Library/Make (Goldsmiths College) - to explore and experiment within the archive and write a script to be performed at South London Gallery. Four new works will be produced. I will have an exhibition at WAL & art pages in Feminist Review.'),
(18669396, '', 'Applicant 3639', 1858497, 'The Moriarty Press', 28, 3.0, 'Yes', 'REJECTED', 0, 0, 17, 'Q3', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 0, 'Individual', 'South West', 'St Ives', 'Cornwall and Isles of Scilly', 'Cornwall', 0, 'N', 0, '6 weeks', 3, 1, 1, 'Ot', 'Literature', '#REF!', 'South West', 'I am a professional writer and wish to establish an electronic publishing house. This will: a) monetise and extend access to my backlist of published books b) build the reputation and readership for my printed books by launching new follow-on titles under my own e-print in the future.'),
(18669827, '', 'Applicant 3640', 18669825, 'Market Development  2011', 28, 2.0, 'No', 'REJECTED', 0, 0, 1, 'Q3', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 0, 'Individual', 'North West', 'Tatton', 'Cheshire', 'Cheshire East', 0, 'N', 0, '6 weeks', 5, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Visual arts', '#REF!', 'North West', 'My application is for funding for  three contemporary craft  fairs this year.  This market development exercise is to help me test possible options and launch my practice. I have been accepted onto the Crafts Council Hothouse programme this year, so this will also help me assess these opportunities thoroughly.'),
(18669934, '', 'Applicant 3641', 18669927, 'Inside', 28, 10.0, 'No', 'OFFERED', 10, 10, 8, 'Q3', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 1, 'Organisation', 'North West', 'Manchester Central', 'Greater Manchester', 'Manchester', 23, 'N', 1, '6 weeks', 6, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Visual arts', '#REF!', 'North West', 'The application will support the development and facilitation of Inside, an exhibition to take place at BLANKSPACE, Manchester between January-February 2012. Through immersing the participant within the viewing space, Inside will explore the psychological connection between the audience and work, demonstrating art''s ability to unsettle, move and disturb.'),
(18670116, '', 'Applicant 3642', 18670114, 'The Lost Generation', 28, 9.0, 'No', 'REJECTED', 0, 0, 8, 'Q3', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 0, 'Individual', 'North West', 'Blackley and Broughton', 'Greater Manchester', 'Salford', 0, 'N', 0, '6 weeks', 6, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Theatre', '#REF!', 'North West', 'The Lost Generation is a Transmedia project combining elements of promenade theatre, none-linear theatre, street theatre, artistic installation, site-specific theatre and new media technology.  The project will explore the proposition that the media acts as an unseen filter on the information from which citizens make their decisions'),
(18670182, '', 'Applicant 3643', 18670180, 'OFFRET', 28, 4.0, 'No', 'REJECTED', 0, 0, 1, 'Q3', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 0, 'Individual', 'London', 'Bermondsey and Old Southwark', 'Greater London', 'Southwark', 0, 'N', 0, '6 weeks', 5, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Literature', '#REF!', 'London', 'Offret is a processual urban intervention in Clapham Junction, one of the areas most affected by UK riots. The project is staging workshops at which local residents consider the various standpoints of the people involved, and jointly elaborate on visions for the future, which will be edited into a newspaper. \n'),
(18671670, '', 'Applicant 3644', 13047652, 'Glasgow International Festival of Visual Art 2012', 29, 2.0, 'No', 'OFFERED', 2, 2, 7, 'Q3', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 1, 'Organisation', 'London', 'Bethnal Green and Bow', 'Greater London', 'Tower Hamlets', 0, 'N', 1, '6 weeks', 6, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Visual arts', '#REF!', 'London', 'For GI 2012, Volume will occupy the Queens Park Railway Club. Using the occasion of the festival, we will work with London based artists James Thomas and Solina Hi-Fi to develop a visual and sonic installation inside the space and a further event in the Queens Park Pub.\n\n \n\n'),
(18672526, '', 'Applicant 3645', 18672523, 'Why anyone would be an actor?', 29, 2.0, 'Yes', 'REJECTED', 0, 0, 7, 'Q3', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 0, 'Individual', 'North West', 'Liverpool, Walton', 'Merseyside', 'Liverpool', 0, 'N', 0, '6 weeks', 1, 1, 1, 'Ot', 'Theatre', '#REF!', 'North West', 'A one act musical play, which I have written to showcase all of my own and 2 more actors talents. I would like to perform this in venues such as the Lowry in Manchester. There are 3 actors involved, including myself. The money will be for props, venue, promotion, costumes.'),
