(18764619, '', 'Applicant 3814', 18764612, 'Origins', 11, 9.0, 'No', 'REJECTED', 0, 0, 30, 'Q4', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 0, 'Organisation', 'Eastern', 'Colchester', 'Essex', 'Colchester', 0, 'Y', 0, '6 weeks', 16, 0, 0, 'Ot', 'Music', '#REF!', 'East', 'I want to present a show incorporating both Native American art forms and traditional gypsy flamenco in Colchester.  This project fits in with the three core values and at five themes of the Cultural Olympiad 2012.   It is intended to inspire and involve young people.'),
(18765907, '', 'Applicant 3815', 1834383, 'Sandblasting Equipment', 11, 4.0, 'No', 'REJECTED', 4, 0, 15, 'Q3', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 0, 'Individual', 'Yorkshire and The Humber', 'Scarborough and Whitby', 'North Yorkshire', 'Scarborough', 0, 'N', 0, '6 weeks', 5, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Visual arts', '#REF!', 'Yorkshire', 'Purchase of a sandblasting booth plus equipment for my architectural glass business.'),
(18766068, '', 'Applicant 3816', 18766062, 'The Doomsday Tablet', 11, 2.0, 'No', 'REJECTED', 0, 0, 16, 'Q3', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 0, 'Individual', 'London', 'Carshalton and Wallington', 'Greater London', 'Sutton', 0, 'N', 0, '6 weeks', 5, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Visual arts', '#REF!', 'London', 'Creating / writing  a children''s photographic comic book.  I''m seeking funding for research / photographic trips to Hadrian''s Wall (where a large part of the book is set) and to update my camera to a Digital SLR.'),
(18767091, '', 'Applicant 3817', 18767084, 'The Travelling Treasury', 11, 10.0, 'No', 'REJECTED', 10, 0, 15, 'Q3', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 0, 'Organisation', 'West Midlands', 'Kenilworth and Southam', 'Warwickshire', 'Warwick', 0, 'N', 0, '6 weeks', 5, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Theatre', '#REF!', 'West Midlands', 'For this application we are proposing a pilot project to create a pop-up temporary theatre on a Routemaster bus. Being a bus we are able to site the work in the best location within Coventry City Centre to allow easy access to a cross section of the community.\n\n'),
(18767199, '', 'Applicant 3818', 18767197, 'Somatic Movement and Costume Research Project', 11, 4.0, 'No', 'REJECTED', 4, 0, 16, 'Q3', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 0, 'Individual', 'London', 'Cities of London and Westminster', 'Greater London', 'Westminster', 0, 'N', 0, '6 weeks', 5, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Combined arts', '#REF!', 'London', 'This R&D aims to explore how costume can affect how we move and perceive and what we create and perform. The project consists of an artist residency between one performance artist and two costume designers and a series of free workshops engaging between 80-100 members of the public.'),
(18768680, '', 'Applicant 3819', 18768678, 'PhD in creative writing at Bath Spa University', 11, 10.0, 'Yes', 'REJECTED', 0, 0, 13, 'Q3', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 0, 'Individual', 'South West', 'Bath', 'Bath and North East Somerset', 'Bath and North East Somerset', 0, 'Y', 0, '6 weeks', 0, 1, 1, 'Ot', 'Literature', '#REF!', 'South West', 'I started a PhD in creative writing at Bath Spa University on April 1st 2011. I am writing a novel on female on male domestic abuse and a supporting critical piece, both of which I hope will advance gender studies/issues in the United Kingdom.'),
(18770244, '', 'Applicant 3820', 8277392, 'The Sunshine Project for South Wiltshire', 11, 4.0, 'No', 'OFFERED', 4, 4, 15, 'Q3', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 1, 'Organisation', 'South West', 'Salisbury', 'Wiltshire', 'Wiltshire', 30, 'N', 1, '6 weeks', 5, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Visual arts', '#REF!', 'South West', 'Create new Y.P. art volunteers (some issued) also mature art volunteers to support an artist to deliver 20 (point of need) Elderly Batik Flag making rural/urban workshops located across South Wilts all leading to a large public access installation of all works in the Cloisters of Salisbury Cathedral'),
(18770391, '', 'Applicant 3821', 9421331, 'Beside The Sea', 11, 10.0, 'No', 'OFFERED', 10, 10, 14, 'Q3', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 1, 'Organisation', 'Eastern', 'Suffolk Coastal', 'Suffolk', 'Waveney', 22, 'Y', 1, '6 weeks', 5, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Theatre', '#REF!', 'East', 'To develop, rehearse and then publicly preview at the Southbank Centre''s Women of the World Festival (mid-March2012) a production of Beside The Sea; a stage adaptation of the revered 2001 French novel by Veronique Olmi.'),
(18771700, '', 'Applicant 3822', 8790402, 'Headingley Litfest:  Lingo', 11, 3.0, 'No', 'OFFERED', 3, 3, 15, 'Q3', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 1, 'Organisation', 'Yorkshire and The Humber', 'Leeds North West', 'West Yorkshire', 'Leeds', 8, 'Y', 1, '6 weeks', 5, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Literature', '#REF!', 'Yorkshire', 'Our fifth Litfest will further develop the work we have done with a range of local creative writers, young poets, a theatre group and musicians through workshops and performance and local and national authors. Our 2012 theme looks at interpreting words in all their variety, from local to global.'),
(18771793, '', 'Applicant 3823', 1622917, 'TATTON PARK BIENNIAL 2012: Flights of Fancy', 11, 100.0, 'No', 'OFFERED', 100, 100, 14, 'Q3', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', 'National activities', 1, 'Organisation', 'North West', 'Tatton', 'Cheshire', 'Cheshire East', 23, 'Y', 1, '12 weeks', 9, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Visual arts', '#REF!', 'North West', 'The third edition of Tatton Park Biennial considers flight with up to twenty new commissions from emerging local and established international artists, all responding to the historic, rural site. The Biennial will engage visitors from divergent groups with an active programme of events and workshops throughout the summer of 2012.'),
(18771907, '', 'Applicant 3824', 1592421, 'Institute of Mental Health sculpture Engagement', 11, 9.0, 'No', 'OFFERED', 9, 9, 21, 'Q3', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 1, 'Organisation', 'East Midlands', 'Nottingham South', 'Nottingham', 'Nottingham', 31, 'N', 1, '6 weeks', 6, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Visual arts', '#REF!', 'East Midlands', 'A public engagement programme  around a new sculpture at the opening of the new Institute of Mental Health on Jubilee Campus, Nottingham, to be inspired by, and reflect the impact of, mental ill-health; local mental health groups will be involved in the artist selection, design and construction process.'),
(18772011, '', 'Applicant 3825', 1857751, '`A BRUSH WITH IMMORTALITY', 11, 26.0, 'No', 'REJECTED', 26, 0, 14, 'Q3', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', 'National activities', 0, 'Individual', 'South West', 'Bristol West', 'Bristol, City of', 'Bristol, City of', 0, 'N', 0, '12 weeks', 9, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Visual arts', '#REF!', 'South West', '''A Brush with Immortality'' is a mixed-media exhibition involving painting, 3D images, film and installation.  Through a fusion of art and science it explores the deeply affecting story of Henrietta Lacks, a young African-American woman, whose death sixty years ago led to ground breaking advances in modern medicine.'),
(18772132, '', 'Applicant 3826', 1670294, 'Soundwaves Festival 2012', 11, 35.0, 'No', 'OFFERED', 0, 0, 21, 'Q3', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 2, 'Organisation', 'South East', 'Brighton, Pavilion', 'Brighton and Hove', 'Brighton and Hove', 0, 'N', 1, '12 weeks', 10, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Music', '#REF!', 'South East', 'Soundwaves Festival creates a platform for cutting edge music and sound art rarely heard anywhere else in the South East. It takes music outside conventional concert settings into innovative multi art events making new music accessible. It provides artists with a space to create pioneering work and develop their practice.'),
(18772209, '', 'Applicant 3827', 12807764, '''Schools on Stage'', London A Cappella Festival', 11, 1.0, 'Yes', 'REJECTED', 0, 0, 19, 'Q3', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 0, 'Organisation', 'London', 'Bermondsey and Old Southwark', 'Greater London', 'Southwark', 0, 'Y', 0, '6 weeks', 1, 1, 1, 'Ot', 'Music', '#REF!', 'London', 'The activity will be a day of workshops, insight events and collaborative performances for between 3 and 6 school a cappella choirs from the UK, hosted at King''s Place in London as part of the London  A Cappella Festival 2012 and led by members of the Swingle Singers.'),
(18774741, '', 'Applicant 3828', 18774733, 'Dawlish Learning Partnership Cultural Olympiad', 12, 7.0, 'No', 'OFFERED', 7, 7, 15, 'Q3', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 1, 'Organisation', 'South West', 'Newton Abbot', 'Devon', 'Teignbridge', 16, 'Y', 1, '6 weeks', 5, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Not art form specific', '#REF!', 'South West', 'This project aims to be part of the official 2012 Cultural Olympiad using this exciting event to celebrate and inspire people in the local community in the Arts.\nThe project will bring together a partnership of schools, universities and local musicians and artists.'),
(18774846, '', 'Applicant 3829', 18774839, 'Life Force Magazine', 11, 92.0, 'Yes', 'REJECTED', 0, 0, 19, 'Q3', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 0, 'Organisation', 'South West', 'Newton Abbot', 'Devon', 'Teignbridge', 0, 'N', 0, '12 weeks', 1, 1, 1, 'Ot', 'Visual arts', '#REF!', 'South West', 'A free online only magazine celebrating the art-form of the photo-essay.  It is monthly and has already become more popular than Richard Branson''s online magazine ''Project''. We are (non-financially) supported by Stephen Fry and other big name photographers such as Rankin, RAX, Larry Fink, David Eustace.'),
