(18967130, '', 'Applicant 4156', 18967122, 'Touring show of The Tempest', 31, 14.0, 'No', 'OFFERED', 14, 14, 12, 'Q4', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 1, 'Organisation', 'Eastern', 'Braintree', 'Essex', 'Braintree', 30, 'N', 1, '12 weeks', 10, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Theatre', '#REF!', 'East', 'Father Hen has been set up to research and develop new systems of rehearsal. We are highly innovative and experimental in exploring a new type of practice in working with text. We want to put on a production of Shakespeare''s ''The Tempest'' with four actors.'),
(18973494, '', 'Applicant 4157', 14594639, 'Critical publication for the North East', 1, 9.0, 'No', 'REJECTED', 0, 0, 6, 'Q3', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 0, 'Organisation', 'North East', 'Newcastle upon Tyne East', 'Tyne and Wear', 'Newcastle upon Tyne', 0, 'Y', 0, '6 weeks', 5, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Literature', '#REF!', 'North East', 'The proposed activity is to introduce a new critical publication in collaboration with Gallery North for the North East which will include reviews and discussions with exhibiting artists as well as provide information about other arts events in the region and acting as a critical forum for contemporary artistic debate.'),
(18974678, '', 'Applicant 4158', 8819269, 'Driving Insipration - Around the Globe', 1, 95.0, 'No', 'OFFERED', 95, 95, 25, 'Q4', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 1, 'Organisation', 'South East', 'Aylesbury', 'Buckinghamshire', 'Aylesbury Vale', 27, 'Y', 1, '12 weeks', 12, 0, 0, 'Ot', 'Visual arts', '#REF!', 'South East', 'The creation of a global animation using disabled artists and Paralympians giving online assemblies and  interviews working with 14 UK and 10 international schools drawing on, developing and showcasing the earlier project work. \nAction research into the sustainability of projects for 2012 linked with Stoke Mandeville''s paralympic heritage.'),
(18976300, '', 'Applicant 4159', 6954928, '4 Puppetised Jackets', 1, 9.0, 'No', 'OFFERED', 9, 9, 6, 'Q3', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 1, 'Individual', 'East Midlands', 'Nottingham East', 'Nottingham', 'Nottingham', 12, 'Y', 1, '6 weeks', 5, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Visual arts', '#REF!', 'East Midlands', 'I will Puppetise. Imbue with the qualities of a Puppet. Four Men''s Jackets. Utilizing input from art goers and the general Public. I will then exhibit them in a vacant Nottingham City Centre Shop. Advancing Puppetry and Contemporary Art.  Challenging the perception of both. Founding a new Arts Business.'),
(18977726, '', 'Applicant 4160', 18977718, 'Organisational Development of Assemble Studio CIC', 1, 10.0, 'Yes', 'REJECTED', 0, 0, 4, 'Q3', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 0, 'Organisation', 'London', 'Hackney South and Shoreditch', 'Greater London', 'Hackney', 0, 'Y', 0, '6 weeks', 0, 1, 1, 'Ot', 'Visual arts', '#REF!', 'London', 'Assemble''s design-and-build work is focused on transforming disused urban spaces, creating fantastic places for community and cultural use and involving the public in the ongoing realization of their work.'),
