(18979173, '', 'Applicant 4168', 10183173, 'New Show ''Birdhouse''', 1, 9.0, 'No', 'OFFERED', 9, 9, 7, 'Q3', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 1, 'Organisation', 'South West', 'Totnes', 'Devon', 'South Hams', 3, 'N', 1, '6 weeks', 5, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Theatre', '#REF!', 'South West', '''Birdhouse'' is a proposal to research and develop a new show by Jammy Voo Theatre.  We are proposing two phases of work in which to fully realise the production.  This application will be for Phase 1 of the research and development process.'),
(18979269, '', 'Applicant 4169', 18979267, 'subtext: black market tale traders', 2, 7.0, 'No', 'REJECTED', 7, 0, 7, 'Q3', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 0, 'Individual', 'London', 'Holborn and St Pancras', 'Greater London', 'Camden', 0, 'Y', 0, '6 weeks', 5, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Theatre', '#REF!', 'London', 'Piece of Cake is looking to reinterpret the Jewish holiday of Purim. Subtext: Black Market Tale traders will be an evening of immersive promenade theatre featuring new writers and drawing new audiences into the arts through the transformation of an unusual space.  \n'),
(18979352, '', 'Applicant 4170', 18979345, 'Art Take-Away & organisational development funding', 1, 10.0, 'No', 'REJECTED', 0, 0, 6, 'Q3', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 0, 'Organisation', 'South East', 'Henley', 'Oxfordshire', 'South Oxfordshire', 0, 'N', 0, '6 weeks', 5, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Visual arts', '#REF!', 'South East', 'An exhibition of 15 artists who''s work will feature in a take-away menu.The work has to fit inside a Take-Away carton. ''Customers'' will choose art they want from the menu by fulfilling a pledge. The pledge will be the `currency'),
(18979551, '', 'Applicant 4171', 1613826, 'Production of Duane Hopkins'' Rapture:Ingland', 1, 29.0, 'No', 'OFFERED', 29, 29, 10, 'Q4', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 1, 'Organisation', 'North East', 'Newcastle upon Tyne East', 'Tyne and Wear', 'Newcastle upon Tyne', 30, 'N', 1, '12 weeks', 10, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Visual arts', '#REF!', 'North East', 'Our activity is the production of a collection of moving image art works by Duane Hopkins, entitled Rapture:Ingland. Rapture:Ingland will present moving image portraits, both real time and extreme-slow-motion, concentrating on economically challenged wards of post-industrial England.'),
(18980570, '', 'Applicant 4172', 1782352, 'Personal and artistic development', 2, 10.0, 'No', 'OFFERED', 10, 10, 6, 'Q3', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 1, 'Individual', 'East Midlands', 'Nottingham East', 'Nottingham', 'Nottingham', 16, 'N', 1, '6 weeks', 5, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Visual arts', '#REF!', 'East Midlands', 'In 2012 I have show in a major national gallery (Nottingham Contemporary), for me this is a significant opportunity to create a new artwork and to present this work before a new audience. In December 2011 I will be relocating to Primary, where I wish to develop my professional practice.'),
(18980781, '', 'Applicant 4173', 15806413, 'Henry V - Theatre Delicatessen', 1, 35.0, 'No', 'REJECTED', 35, 0, 25, 'Q4', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 0, 'Organisation', 'West Midlands', 'West Worcestershire', 'Worcestershire', 'Wychavon', 0, 'N', 0, '12 weeks', 12, 0, 0, 'Ot', 'Theatre', '#REF!', 'West Midlands', 'To stage an immersive production of Shakespeare''s Henry V in a non-theatre space within central London for 8 weeks.\n\nUtilising elements of promenade performance, we will create a radical re-interpretation of Shakespeare''s rousing depiction of warfare and leadership, exploring the necessity and impact of armed conflict.'),
(18980882, '', 'Applicant 4174', 1618861, 'Cloud Child - early years theatre play', 30, 4.0, 'No', 'OFFERED', 4, 4, 7, 'Q3', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 1, 'Organisation', 'North West', 'Blackpool North and Cleveleys', 'Lancashire', 'Wyre', 23, 'N', 1, '6 weeks', 5, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Theatre', '#REF!', 'North West', 'Research and development of interactive theatre play performance for early years children in partnership with the Lowry. Early years groups in Salford willl be involved in this process, helping DNA to develop ideas for a touring performance and E.Y providers will also be invited to undertake specialist  professional development.'),
(18981010, '', 'Applicant 4175', 18981003, 'Saffron Recording Project', 1, 5.0, 'No', 'REJECTED', 0, 0, 6, 'Q3', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 0, 'Organisation', 'East Midlands', 'Leicester South', 'Leicester', 'Leicester', 0, 'N', 0, '6 weeks', 5, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Music', '#REF!', 'East Midlands', 'I propose to deliver a music recording project for the underprivileged yet talented youths within the deprived area of "Saffron Lane".\n\n'),
