(19368081, '', 'Applicant 4888', 1846196, 'STILL-NIGHT', 13, 8.0, 'No', 'OFFERED', 8, 8, 18, 'Q4', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 1, 'Individual', 'South East', 'Woking', 'Surrey', 'Woking', 9, 'N', 1, '6 weeks', 5, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Theatre', '#REF!', 'South East', 'An eight week development and rehearsals towards creation of a new theatre show, by Silvia Mercuriali and Gemma Brockis, where the city in which the show happens is the central character of a narrative that fuses real life facts with mythic storytelling. Based on Italo Calvino''s ''Invisible Cities''.'),
(19368894, '', 'Applicant 4889', 19368887, 'Luton Mela', 12, 77.0, 'No', 'OFFERED', 77, 77, 23, 'Q4', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 1, 'Organisation', 'Eastern', 'Luton North', 'Luton', 'Luton', 0, 'Y', 1, '12 weeks', 10, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Combined arts', '#REF!', 'East', 'Development and presentation of a high quality, innovative and exciting artistic programme at Luton Mela 2012, which is an integral part of the Love Luton 2012 Festival. This will be complemented by a community engagement programme, capacity building for artists, and organisational development, leading up to Luton Mela in 2013.'),
(19370499, '', 'Applicant 4890', 1606402, 'CompanyWise', 13, 7.0, 'No', 'OFFERED', 7, 7, 24, 'Q4', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 1, 'Organisation', 'London', 'Cities of London and Westminster', 'Greater London', 'Westminster', 1, 'N', 1, '6 weeks', 6, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Theatre', '#REF!', 'London', 'CompanyWise teaches Years 9-13 drama students the principles of being a production company through a practical, 6-8 week mentoring project with professional theatre companies. In addition to developing team-building, creative and management skills, CompanyWise will provide `an insider'),
