(19383424, '', 'Applicant 4913', 19383422, 'The Ginger Tea Tour', 13, 4.0, 'No', 'OFFERED', 4, 4, 25, 'Q4', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 1, 'Individual', 'London', 'Lewisham, Deptford', 'Greater London', 'Lewisham', 15, 'Y', 1, '6 weeks', 6, 0, 0, 'Ot', 'Music', '#REF!', 'London', 'East London, hosting the Olympics and known to have poor participation in the arts, is the focus of our music tour of independent coffee shops. \n\nThe Ginger Tea Tour, named after a Ugandan drink, will encourage multicultural understanding, and engage more locals in music leading up to the Cultural Olympiad.\n'),
(19383528, '', 'Applicant 4914', 19383521, 'All Pieces Together', 13, 3.0, 'No', 'REJECTED', 0, 0, 18, 'Q4', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 0, 'Organisation', 'North West', 'Wallasey', 'Merseyside', 'Wirral', 0, 'N', 0, '6 weeks', 5, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Visual arts', '#REF!', 'North West', 'Our activity aims to enable our school community to learn how to create a mosaic and then have this piece displayed in The Williamson Art Gallery. We want the participants to experience the creative process from design conception through to the unveiling of a finished piece.'),
(19383597, '', 'Applicant 4915', 19383595, 'Mama Tokus: Gospel Truths', 13, 9.0, 'No', 'REJECTED', 9, 0, 18, 'Q4', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 0, 'Individual', 'South West', 'Totnes', 'Devon', 'South Hams', 0, 'N', 0, '6 weeks', 5, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Theatre', '#REF!', 'South West', 'To develop then perform a sustainable one-woman-show for beyond theatres incorporating autobiographical experiences as a black musician, that catalyses audiences to make song, community links and personal change, whilst professionally developing myself as a businesslike artiste-producer through co-production with the Barbican Theatre''s Flourish development programme.'),
(19383951, '', 'Applicant 4916', 19054984, 'Titanic Commemorative Sculpture', 13, 10.0, 'No', 'OFFERED', 10, 10, 18, 'Q4', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 1, 'Individual', 'North West', 'Wirral South', 'Merseyside', 'Wirral', 2, 'N', 1, '6 weeks', 5, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Visual arts', '#REF!', 'North West', 'My activity is the design and build of a sculpture to commemorate the 100th anniversary of the sinking of the Titanic, combined with a programme of learning and engagement working with schools, the local Council, community, tourists, and Port Sunlight Village Trust.'),
(19384071, '', 'Applicant 4917', 19384069, 'Photography', 13, 1.0, 'No', 'REJECTED', 0, 0, 18, 'Q4', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 0, 'Individual', 'South West', 'Tiverton and Honiton', 'Devon', 'Mid Devon', 0, 'N', 0, '6 weeks', 5, 1, 0, 'Ot', 'Visual arts', '#REF!', 'South West', 'I am an out of work Graphic Designer, and to keep myself occupied, I have threw myself back into my hobby of photography. The images that have created more attention than any others have been my floral images enhanced through photoshop, when uploaded onto a forum display site called ePHOTOzine.'),
