(19421123, '', 'Applicant 4973', 13300145, 'MAN - Development of touring activity', 16, 8.0, 'No', 'REJECTED', 0, 0, 1, 'Q4', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 0, 'Organisation', 'East Midlands', 'Leicester South', 'Leicester', 'Leicester', 0, 'N', 0, '6 weeks', 7, 0, 0, 'Ot', 'Combined arts', '#REF!', 'East Midlands', 'We would like to build on our wide-ranging performance work to date by beginning to develop relationships with more traditional performance venues and their audiences by working with a Tour Booker and creating and presenting a new piece of performance work, MAN.'),
(19421807, '', 'Applicant 4974', 1839230, 'MORE GORGEOUS - Visual arts performance', 16, 9.0, 'No', 'REJECTED', 0, 0, 31, 'Q4', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 0, 'Individual', 'Yorkshire and The Humber', 'Kingston upon Hull North', 'Kingston upon Hull, City of', 'Kingston upon Hull, City of', 0, 'N', 0, '6 weeks', 7, 0, 0, 'Ot', 'Combined arts', '#REF!', 'Yorkshire', 'A collaboration of six performers and artists, MORE GORGEOUS is a multi-creative show, with physical theatre, mime, dance, installation, and puppets.  Controversial and comedic, MORE GORGEOUS explores themes of beauty. It includes live performance in public venues and intensive workshops in schools, colleges and youth groups addressing body image.'),
(19422455, '', 'Applicant 4975', 1628506, 'Yardstick', 16, 9.0, 'No', 'OFFERED', 9, 9, 1, 'Q4', '2011/2012', '2011/2012', 'Lottery', 'Grants for the arts', '', 1, 'Organisation', 'South West', 'Bristol West', 'Bristol, City of', 'Bristol, City of', 8, 'Y', 1, '6 weeks', 7, 0, 0, 'Ot', 'Literature', '#REF!', 'South West', 'Our activities will expand the Black cultural offer and diversify audiences attending live literature events in a library setting in the Bristol and Bath city-region. We will include a participative creative writing workshop with a high profile Black author to support the professional development of emerging talent.'),
